title: crunchy topped rhubarb muffins
directions: Combine sugar, oil, egg, buttermilk and vanilla. Sift flour, soda and salt together and stir into liquid mixture. Blend in nuts and rhubarb. Spoon into greased muffin tins 2/3 full. Sprinkle with topping. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: lemon delight
directions: Blend margarine, flour, nuts, pat into bottom of 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and whipped topping. Spread over crust.
Mix pudding with milk, pour over cheese layer. Chill well.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: portuguese donuts(filkos)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, butter and yeast dissolved in water. Add lemon rind and salt.
Mix well, beating until light.
Add flour.
Knead for 15 minutes or until dough is smooth.
Don't leave dough too soft.
Cover with cloth.
Let dough rise to double in bulk.
Heat oil in a deep pan.
Have plenty of oil, keeping heat about medium to low.
Make donuts, about 1/3 cup each.
Stick finger through the center of dough to stretch the hole or just spoon dough in hot oil.
Fry until golden, turning once. Remove from oil.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs
with
sugar
until
creamy.
Add
to cottage cheese, add
flour,
melted
oleo or butter, lemon juice, rind and flavorings.
Beat
until well blended and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie
shell.
Top with graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake
in
oven for 45 minutes or until set and brown.
Optional
but
also good to add 1/2 cup raisins or 1/2 cup Angel Flake coconut.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse.
Cut cheese into cubes; put in pan with macaroni.
Pour enough milk into pan to cover macaroni. Simmer until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Then pour into 9 x 13-inch pan; crush saltines over top and bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off green peppers.
Remove seeds, precook peppers in boiling salted water 5 minutes.
Drain, sprinkle inside with salt.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift together the sugar and flour; set aside.
Mix in a saucepan the margarine, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar and stir.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in greased sheet cake pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch).
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Place icing on cake after it has cooled about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: juanita's pie crust
directions: *Note:
Some brands of flour may need a little more ice water.

title: loin of venison with cherry chili salsa
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Rinse and dry the venison.
Tie with a string so that it is of uniform thickness.
Lightly season with salt and pepper.
Heat a saute pan with a thin coating of olive oil.
When olive oil is hot (not smoking), add venison and brown on all sides, then place the venison in a casserole in the oven for 15 to 25 minutes or until medium rare.
Allow venison to rest at room temperature for at least 20 minutes before cutting into thin slices to serve.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Melt cheese.
Add mayonnaise; stir until smooth.
Add potatoes; crumble bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes or until bubbly and slightly brown on top.

title: fresh vegetable sauté
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet on medium-high heat. Add vegetables; cook and stir until tender crisp.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Remove seeds from pumpkin; wash seeds.
Place seeds on well oiled cookie sheet.
Salt seeds.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: yum-yums
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together; set aside.
Cream butter and vanilla until butter softens.
Add sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients in fourths to creamed mixture, beating just until blended.
Form dough into balls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Roll in additional sugar.
Place about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden.
Place a chocolate kiss on top after baking.
Makes about 10 dozen cookies.

title: peanut-butter fudge
directions: Cook the sugar, milk and butter until it forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water.
Beat in peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Use electric beater.
Pour into a buttered dish.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and make a hole in the middle of mixture. Add liquids.
Mix together with spoon.
Prepare 2 loaf pans by greasing with oleo and use sugar to coat as you would use flour (sugar spreads nicely).
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
You can also bake this in a coffee can, too.

title: cranberry pudding cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, sour cream, oil and nuts in a large bowl.
Blend and then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Fold in cranberry sauce cubes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean and begins to pull away from sides.
Do not under bake.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: mincemeat pie(very old)
directions: A measure is like 2 cups for 2 measures or 1 for 1.
Any size just as long as it is the same all the way through.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a large saucepan cook sugar, syrup and water until it reaches hard ball stage (250°).
Add peanuts and cook until golden brown.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Add soda and stir well.
Do not stir too long after adding soda.
This is the secret of this candy.
Pour onto a buttered marble slab. Yield:
2 pounds.

title: fudge
directions: Melt all the ingredients in a double boiler until creamy. Pour on a buttered plate.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
The longer left in refrigerator, the firmer.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian nut bread
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add coconut, pineapple and sugar. Sift in dry ingredients.
Spread in greased loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Scrape out pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Chop pulp and combine with rice, onion, pepper, corn, salt and basil.
Place zucchini shells in an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Mound 1/4 of vegetable mixture into each shell.
Top with chopped tomato.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High 5 to 7 minutes or until shells are tender, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 3 minutes or bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes in regular oven.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion, green pepper and salt and pepper. Drain and add to rest of ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: mrs. whalley's date dessert
directions: *Substitute Egg Beaters (3/4 cup) and beat 3 egg whites; discard yolks.

title: steamed fish with dau see (black beans)
directions: Arrange
fish
in
a bowl.
Mix
remaining
ingredients together; sprinkle over fish.
Steam for 15 to
20	minutes or more, depending on size of fish.
When fish
is
cooked, drain the liquid and thicken with cornstarch.
If
necessary,
add a small amount of water.
Transfer fish to a platter; pour gravy over. Garnish with Chinese parsley.

title: passover cookies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar. Mix in oil and matzo meal.
Add nuts and mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Shape into 1/2 teaspoon balls. Put on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until lightly brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together 1 stick melted butter and graham crackers to make crust.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, 2 sticks margarine and 2 eggs with beaters for 15 minutes.
Pour over crust.
Slice bananas over this.
Pour 2 cans crushed pineapple over bananas.
Spread on large carton of Cool Whip over pineapple. Sprinkle with 1 cup pecans and top with cherries.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Marinate 15 chicken wings (30 pieces, cut in half) for 1 hour. Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into ball and roll in pecans.

title: fudge full peanut butter bars
directions: Combine cake mix, peanut butter, melted margarine and eggs. Spread 2/3 of the mixture in the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.

title: chocolate pound cake with nuts on top
directions: Combine butter and shortening, mixing well.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour batter into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle pecans evenly over batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cake cool completely.

title: low-fat chili
directions: Brown ground round slowly.
Add ground turkey until no longer pink. Add vegetables. Cook about 5 minutes. Add tomato sauce. Cook slowly 3 hours.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins for 20 minutes.
Remove raisins from juice and let cool.
You will need 1/2 cup of juice from raisins.
Cream together margarine, eggs, sugar and vanilla, then add raisin juice.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt, soda and spices together. Slowly mix dry ingredients into creamed mixture. When thoroughly mixed add old fashioned oats, nuts and raisins last.
Bake at 400° on top rack for 10 minutes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown meat.
Add all ingredients.
Add water if needed. Simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: 3 layer chocolate cake
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, butter and 1 cup pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: devilish pumpkin bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in pumpkin.
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except for nuts and chocolate chips.
Stir dry ingredients into pumpkin mixture, a little at a time; blend thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour in batter, dividing evenly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until toothpick in center comes out clean.
This can be prepared a day ahead.
Will last 1 to 2 weeks if wrapped and refrigerated.
I've made this every year for over 20 years!

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare lettuce and tomatoes for salad.
Add cheese and corn chips.
You can add kidney beans, olives and radishes.

title: country fried venison "omaha style"
directions: Cut strip of venison away from backbone.
Trim away all fat and white outer layer, for this will make your meat tough if not removed.
Cut the back strap into strips, not too thin, but not too thick either.
Wash meat in cold water and place on board you use to tenderize your meat.
Use your coke bottle (little end) and beat on both sides.
Salt and pepper, dip in flour, then in buttermilk, and back into the flour, coating well.
Have oil hot, medium high, cook until golden brown on both sides.
Serve hot with vegetables, and rolls for divine meal.

title: melting moments
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch and sugar in a bowl.
Blend in butter until a soft dough is formed.
If dough is too soft to handle, cover and chill.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in tightly covered skillet. Cook at 250° until tender.

title: easy brownie or cake frosting
directions: Bring to a quick full boil.
Remove from the heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir in the powdered sugar.
Spread warm frosting on cooled brownies or cake.

title: chewies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar; add beaten eggs.
Add vanilla. Fold in flour, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Spread in well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.
Yields 24 bars.

title: fisherman's delight
directions: Fry sausage and crumble.
Remove from grease.
Fry onions in grease.
Combine all ingredients.
Add sage to taste.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: kool-aid floats
directions: In large pitchers, prepare Kool-Aid with sugar and water according to package directions.
Stir in orange juice concentrate.
Just before serving, add the ginger ale.
Pour into tall glasses.
Add scoops of sherbet to glasses.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: ricotta cheese pie
directions: For crust, stir together flour, sugar and lemon peel.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in 1 egg yolk and vanilla.
Pat 1/3 of the dough onto the bottom of 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 400° about 7 minutes, until golden.
Cool.
Butter sides of pan. Attach to bottom.
Pat remaining dough onto sides of pan to height of 1 1/2 inches.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and food coloring. Add water.
Add vanilla, flour, cocoa and salt together alternately with milk.
Beat 10 minutes.
Last, fold in thoroughly the soda dissolved in vinegar.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with melted butter.
Put half in casserole dish. Mix everything else together.
Pour over stuffing mix.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: secret holiday fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each egg.
Add crumbs, mix well.
Add other ingredients. Bake in tube pan at 350° for 90 minutes, line pan.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Measure sugar.
Take out 2 tablespoons of it and set aside. Cream butter and rest of sugar. Beat in egg yolks.
Add lemon peel.
Stir in flour, just until mixed.
Add milk and lemon juice. Stir well.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Separate rolls into 4 rectangles.
Seal perforations by pressing together.
Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Add chicken.
Mix, then add green peppers, mushrooms, salt, pepper, milk, parsley and chives.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture onto each crescent roll rectangle.
Pull up corners and twist top.
Melt 4 tablespoons of margarine; dip crescents into it and into crushed croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients (flour, salt and baking soda).
Mix all ingredients, except nuts, then add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Soften whipped cream and stir dry Jell-O and cottage cheese in.
Mix completely then stir in whole bag marshmallows. Refrigerate several hours to get firm and serve.

title: crumbled apples
directions: Quarter apples and place in buttered pan.
Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, butter and water.
Pour over apples and bake at 350°. Can be served hot or cold or with milk.

title: andrea's favorite peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Immediately press a chocolate kiss in center of each cookie. Remove to wire racks to cool.
Yield: About 3 dozen.

title: soda cracker pie (mock apple)
directions: Make dough for two crust pie.
Break soda crackers into 4 pieces and put into unbaked pie shell.
Boil together 5 or 10 minutes sugar, cinnamon, cream of tartar, lemon juice and water. Pour hot mixture over crackers.
Put on top crust and bake in hot oven (475°) about 15 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour alternately with the syrup. Add the vanilla. Pour in pan and cook 25 minutes at 350°. It may shake but is completely done at 25 minutes.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple until you have one cup (combined).
If necessary, add enough water to make one cup.
Bring juice to a boil and add jello, stirring until completely dissolved. When cooled, add coke; stir and chill in refrigerator until partly jelled.
Add drained cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into mold that has been rinsed in cold water or in a Tupperware dish with lid.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and beat on medium speed until well mixed. Bake in a 325° oven until done.
Makes 3 large layers.

title: skillet stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, then drain. Add sour cream, soups and water. Bring to a boil.
Add noodles. Cover and simmer until noodles are done, about 20 minutes.

title: simple stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Arrange caps on baking tray. Chop stems.
Put butter, stems, onion, salt and pepper in frying pan.
Fry slowly until onions are clear and soft.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Stuff caps.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes or broil for about 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar and blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add flavoring.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage treats
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage and ground beef; drain fat.
Cube cheese and add to meat mixture over medium-low heat until melty.
Add spices; stir well.
Spread 1 to 2 tablespoons mixture onto each slice cocktail bread and bake uncovered on cookie sheet in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, syrup, sugar, melted butter and vanilla.
Gently stir in pecans.
Pour in a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until set.

title: sweet 'n sour barbecue chicken
directions: Combine preserves, vinegar and onion in a 12 x 7 1/2-inch microwave-safe baking dish.
Add chicken; turn to coat.
Sprinkle with coating mixture, turning to coat evenly.
Cover and cook on High for 6 minutes; rotate dish 1/2 turn and cook 6 more minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: pear relish
directions: Put pears, onions and peppers through a food chopper.
Add vinegar and spice.
Boil for 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: creole bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart glass casserole dish. In large bowl, combine bread and milk and let soak.
In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly; stir in sugar, butter, vanilla and salt. Add to bread mixture; stir to mix.
Pour into dish; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve warm with brandy sauce.

title: quick chicken divan
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish. Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Arrange broccoli in greased baking dish.
Layer chicken over broccoli.
In a small bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; mix well.
Spread over chicken; sprinkle with cheese.

title: "he-man" hamburgers
directions: Combine bread crumbs, milk and beef.
Mix well.
Shape into patties.
Heat fat in skillet.
Brown patties on both sides. Separate onion slices into rings.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat patties.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or more.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat eggs; add oil.
Add sugar slowly, then flour, mixed with dry ingredients.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour in 13 x 9-inch pan.
If using Pyrex, bake at 325°.

title: corn soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan; puree 2 cups milk and corn in small amounts until all pureed.
Add corn mixture, salt and pepper to butter (don't overdo on salt; chips are salty).
Bring to a boil about 5 minutes until slightly thickened.
Mixture will not get real thick.

title: herb jelly
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and heat to a rolling boil. Add fruit pectin and heat to full rolling boil; boil one minute. Remove leaves.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal immediately.

title: pasta with artichoke hearts
directions: Cut artichoke hearts into quarters.
Combine with prosciutto, olives and spaghetti sauce in a medium saucepan and simmer 10 minutes.
Toss with cooked pasta.
Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese on individual servings.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: girl scout stew
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet.
Add onion, salt, pepper and soup.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice or with biscuits.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package; don't add salt.
Drain.
Combine broccoli, soup, mayonnaise, eggs and cheese.
Put in casserole dish; spread crushed crackers on top and then pour melted butter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: calorie conscious stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake or microwave potatoes.
Mash pulp and combine with cottage cheese, tomato, parsley, chives, salt, pepper and dill weed.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and microwave until thoroughly heated.

title: cachapas(corn pancakes)
directions: Cut grains of corn close to the cob and grind very fine in food processor or blender.
Add salt, brown sugar and cream to make a meal the consistency of heavy corn meal.
Place spoonful on buttered sandwich grill and spread thin.
Close grill and wait until slightly browned, about 3 minutes.

title: eclair dessert
directions: In a small saucepan, combine ingredients.
Heat until chips are melted and boil.
Pour over graham crackers.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Best if it can be refrigerated overnight.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine, blend flour, salt and pepper in skillet until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk. Return to heat and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.*
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into ungreased casserole dish and top with sliced almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large saucepan, bring to a boil the margarine, water and cocoa.
Sift together the dry ingredients and stir into boiling mixture (do not beat).
In a small bowl, beat eggs, buttermilk and vanilla together.
Stir into hot mixture.
Pour into pan.
Bake only 20 minutes in a preheated 400° oven.
Frost in the pan with Easy Chocolate Icing while cake is still hot.
When cooled completely, cover tightly.

title: shish kabobs
directions: Rinse pork and beef under cool water.
Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes and marinate per instructions on meat marinade (do not overmarinate).

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour condensed milk over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: swiss cheese broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water for 10 minutes; drain.
In 2-quart pot, melt butter.
Stir in flour and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt until smooth.
Add onions, cook 1 minute.
Preheat oven to 325°. Slowly stir in milk.
When mix thickens, remove from heat.
Stir in cheese and broccoli; stir in eggs.
Pour into greased baking dish, bake 30 minutes or until firm to the touch.

title: fruity dip
directions: With electric mixer, mix cheese for about a minute; add the marshmallow cream and beat until smooth.
Place in a serving bowl; cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
I serve this by placing the bowl in the middle of a tray and arranging the fruit around it.
If you want to add a bit of color, add a drop or two of food coloring while mixing.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook the butter and sugar over high heat until mixture foams vigorously.
Turn heat down low and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the whole almonds.
Stir over high heat until skins begin to pop.
Reduce heat and continue to cook 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into a cookie sheet and cool.
When cool, melt chocolate chips, spread 1/2 of chocolate on one side and sprinkle with 1/2 the chopped nuts.
When chocolate sets, turn candy over and spread with remaining chocolate and nuts.
Break into pieces with sharp object.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil
eggs
and
peel.
Halve eggs, lengthwise.
Remove egg yolks and mash with seasonings and mayonnaise.
Refill egg whites. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: key west ribs
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees. Arrange ribs in 9-inch pan, cover with just enough water to cook. Cook for 30 minutes. Mix ketchup, lime juice, soy sauce and honey in pan; heat until boiling. Pour water off ribs and cover with the sauce. Cook another 1/2 hour or until done end tender.

title: chuckwagon chili
directions: Put bacon and meat in large covered dish and bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Add onions, garlic and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Add other ingredients and bake another hour.

title: lemon blueberry poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Rinse blueberries with cold water and drain.
For loaf, empty muffin mix into medium bowl.
Add poppy seed; stir to combine and break up any lumps.
Add egg and water; stir until moistened, about 50 strokes.
Fold in blueberries and lemon peel. Pour into pan.
Sprinkle topping from packet over batter.
Bake at 350° for 57 to 62 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Loosen loaf from pan.
Lay foil over top when removing from pan to keep topping intact.
Invert onto cooling rack.
Turn right side up.
Cool completely.

title: thumbprints
directions: Mix together all ingredients except egg white, nuts and jelly. Roll into small balls.
Beat egg white until stiff peaks form. Spread the nuts on waxed paper.
Roll each ball in egg white, then in nuts.
Place on cookie sheet and make a thumbprint in each one. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
When completely cool, fill thumbprint with diet jelly.
Diet jelly (teaspoon = 16 calories). Yield:
4 dozen cookies.
Carbohydrate 2.5 g, protein .6 g, fat l.9 g, calories 29.
One cookie = 1/4 bread exchange, 1/4 fat exchange.

title: home-made vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown stewing meat in a large kettle, then add bouillon and boiling water.
Add all your vegetables and simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours on low heat.
You may add 1 cup pasta to soup about 45 minutes before it is finished.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Empty soup mix into saucepan; add milk and water.
Stir until blended.
Cook until comes to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Stir in corned beef, vegetables and pimento.
Put into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle parsley over the top.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 10 minutes until top is golden.

title: crab cakes
directions: Break bread into small pieces and moisten with milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Broil or fry until golden brown on both sides.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together, mixing well.
Place mixture in baking dish. Cover with buttered corn flakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fusilli with chicken and roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix chicken, zucchini, yellow squash, red peppers, salt, pepper, fennel seed, rosemary, garlic and oil in an ungreased 15 x 12-inch baking pan, then spread in a single layer.

title: taco casserole
directions: Put crushed chips on bottom of 10-inch pan.
Brown hamburger and onion; add seasoning and tomatoes.
Pour on top of chips. Spread sour cream; top with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate and vanilla almond bark.
Pour in peanuts. Cool on wax paper.

title: peanut soup
directions: Melt butter in gallon size pot.
Add peanut butter. Stir 3 minutes.
Add flour; stir until golden brown.
Add chicken broth, chicken base and salt.
Cook 25 minutes.
Strain.
Add hot coffee cream and 1 tablespoon of butter.
Stir and serve.

title: chocolate cola cake
directions: Sift the flour and sugar.
Place margarine, cocoa and cola beverage in pan; bring to a boil and add flour mixture.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Batter will be quite thin with marshmallows floating on top.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice when cool with cola icing.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Spoon into a 2-quart casserole dish. Cook for 45 minutes and serve.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, salt and onions.
Beat until fluffy.
Place in buttered casserole dish. (Don't fill too full because it raises.) Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat butter until light and fluffy and gradually beat in sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla. Stir into flour mixture until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put all ingredients into a large salad bowl.
Toss; refrigerate until chilled.
Serve.
This is a great salad for a hot, summer day.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix pumpkin, water, oil and eggs together.
Pour into dry mixture and mix well.
Pour into two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven (preheated) for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle of loaf comes out clean.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: five minute cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage for 2 minutes in hot milk.
Add cream, blended butter and flour plus seasonings.
Cook rapidly for 3 to 4 minutes and serve.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs. Add dry ingredients. Mix well. Fold in raisins, nuts and apples.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple with pudding.
Let stand for 1/2 hour, until thick.
Add all other ingredients.
Decorate with whole walnuts and cherries.

title: roast beef quesadillas
directions: Place onion and bell pepper in small microwave-safe bowl. Cover and microwave at High 3 to 4 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time. Stir in 3 tablespoons salsa; reserve. Sprinkle equal amount of cheese evenly on each tortilla. Arrange deli roast beef over cheese; top with equal amount of reserved vegetable mixture. Fold tortillas over to close.

title: fideo
directions: Cook ground beef with onions; half way through cooking the meat, begin cooking Fideo vermicelli.
To make Fideo, boil about 4 quarts (hard boil).
Then drop in Fideo; cook hard for 3 minutes, constantly stirring.
When done, drain water off Fideo and set aside.
When beef is done, drain fat.
Season to taste with garlic, pepper, salt and seasoned salt.
Return to stove and stir in seasonings well; then add tomato sauce, tomatoes and Fideo.
Stir well; cook until it bubbles.
Eat Fideo with tortillas.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Salt shrimp in large baking pan for 1 hour.
In a pot heat all other ingredients.
Pour over salty shrimp and bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until shrimp are all cooked.

title: taco salad
directions: Stir together beef, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and salt.
Mix all together with mixture and store in refrigerator until served.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate bits and water in double boiler.
Add sugar and mix well.
Remove from heat; add egg yolks and cool.
Beat egg whites to peaks.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Beat 1 pint of cream with vanilla.
Fold into chocolate mixture and chill for 24 hours.
Whip the remaining 1 pint of cream for a garnish on top of mousse.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 40 minutes at 300°.
Serve with unsweetened applesauce, if desired.

title: portuguese kidney bean soup
directions: Put beans in a large pan with 4 cups water. Saut onion and garlic in bacon fat in another pan. Add to pot and add potatoes, tomato paste, bay leaves, allspice, salt and pepper. Simmer 45 minutes to an hour, adding more liquid if necessary; it should be thick. This should serve four. You improvise sometimes by adding corn, ground meat, anything that sounds good.

title: spareribs
directions: Cook spareribs until well done.
Add sparerib sauce, water, brown sugar and syrup; bring to boil and stir well.
Place ribs in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour sauce over.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: citrus punch
directions: Mix frozen punch with 2 cans water; mix thoroughly.
If you want to add any optional juices, mix them in now with 2 cans water. Then add 7-Up slowly so not to ruin bubbles.
Add ice and serve. If you want to add ice cream, omit ice and float your favorite ice cream on top.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream the cheese; add soup, shrimp and onions.

title: bavarian potato soup
directions: In covered saucepan, bring 3 cups water to a boil.
Add vegetables and simmer until tender, approximately 25 minutes. Pour water and press vegetables through a metal strainer, pureeing vegetables.
Set water/vegetable mixture aside.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
After potatoes are cool, slice them, not too thin.
Add diced onions, celery, green pepper, eggs, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Fry bacon until crisp; pour bacon and grease ** over the potatoes.
Add vinegar, water and sugar to the skillet you just took bacon out of.
When this comes to a boil, add flour and water* to the mixture just as you would for gravy.
This will make the mixture just a little thicker so it will adhere to the potatoes.
Pour over potatoes and toss well. Let potato salad stand for about 2 hours.
Taste; it more than likely will have absorbed enough of the mixture that it is not as tart as you would like it.
Again just heat a little vinegar (use your own judgment) water and sugar and pour over the potatoes again until your taste is satisfied.

title: ground beef grand style
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix together milk, salt and ketchup.
Mix together hamburger and ketchup mixture.
Add cream cheese and cream of mushroom soup.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then put biscuits on top and bake another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: gingerbread cobbler
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, juice and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Pour into 12 x 7 baking dish.
In mixing bowl, combine gingerbread mix, milk and oil; stir.
Drop by spoonfuls over hot syrup.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chinese style fried rice
directions: In small saucepan, bring 1 cup water to a boil.
Add rice. Remove from heat, cover and let stand 5 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook rice. Mix all ingredients together and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Cook for 35 minutes at 350°.
Can be topped with buttered cracker crumbs or bread crumbs.

title: golden potato medley
directions: Cut
potatoes
into 1-inch cubes; slice carrots.
Cover with boiling
water
and
simmer
until
both
vegetables are tender, 15 minutes; drain.
Melt butter in saucepan; add onion and
green pepper.
Saute until onion is tender; blend in the flour
and add the
milk.
Stir
and
cook
until
thickened. Remove from heat; add
the
pimentos and season with salt and pepper.
Stir in cheese
until blended in.
Turn cooked potatoes and carrots
into buttered
1 1/2 quart casserole.
Pour sauce over and
stir lightly.
Mix
bread crumbs with butter; sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes if baked immediately.
Or, cover and refrigerate until later, then bake for 45 to
minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Double ingredients for 8 servings, but use only 3 1/2 cups of milk.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and dash of salt.
Add corn syrup, butter and pecans.
Pour into deep dish 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar in bowl. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well between each addition.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Allow meat to get to room temperature.
Preheat oven to 425° to 450°.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut stem ends from peppers and remove seed. Put peppers into boiling water and cook for 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from water and drain.

title: parmesan chips
directions: Line a baking pan with parchment paper.
Spread grated cheese on paper, leaving 1/4-inch at edges.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Break into chips.
Good for dips and soups.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Mix together German chocolate cake mix, melted margarine and the other 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Put half cake mixture into pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Put 1 cup chocolate chips over cake mix, then add the caramel mixture and the remainder of cake mixture.
It will be thick so pat it out flat.
Bake for another 18 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli cheddar soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and cook for 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth, lemon juice and cheese and cook for 15 minutes.
(Optional:
puree in blender after cooking.)
Add remaining ingredients to mixture.
Serves 8.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine pasta, tomatoes, broccoli and black beans. Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, garlic, Italian seasoning and pepper.
Pour over salad and toss to coat well. Cover and chill 2 hours.
Yields 10 servings.

title: vegetarian breakfast roll with texturized vegetable protein (tvp)
directions: Brown and crumble breakfast patties with peppers, garlic, onion and black pepper in olive oil (1/2 teaspoon).
Layer 4 to 6 sheets phyllo dough, brushing lightly with olive oil between sheets.
Toss remaining ingredients with patties mixture and place 2 to 3 cups of this mixture in a line at the end of the sheet of dough.
Roll up sealing the ends.
Brush lightly with oil.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: easy tea cakes
directions: Mix eggs, Wesson oil and vanilla, then add sugar and flour. Roll and cut or make balls and pat out onto pan sprayed with nonstick spray.
Cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Gradually add evaporated milk; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until just done; drain and cool.
Julienne ham, cheese and salami.
In large bowl, combine first 9 items.
Combine next 7 items and mix thoroughly.
Pour over spaghetti mixture. Toss and chill 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: million dollar rice salad
directions: Combine marshmallows and drained pineapple.
Mix cream cheese with sugar and Miracle Whip until smooth.
Add rice and cherries to marshmallow mix.
Fold in whipped cream and nuts.
Chill for several hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage and sauerkraut
directions: Put sausage to cook in cold skillet.
Cook slowly, covered, for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Pour off drippings as they collect.
Cook other ingredients together until browned.
When heated through, serve with hot sausage.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chopstick chicken
directions: Wash, dry, and cut chicken into serving-size pieces.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a shallow baking dish, mix well.
Arrange chicken over rice mixture.
Brush chicken with melted butter or margarine.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for 30 minutes longer, or until chicken and rice are tender.

title: reese's bars
directions: Mix melted butter, peanut butter and vanilla together.
Pat into pan and let sit until cool.
Boil sugar, milk and cocoa.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla and stir.
Pour over crust.
Cut when cool.

title: lemon yummies
directions: Combine cake mix, flour and egg in a large bowl.
Add whipped topping.
Stir until well mixed (do not use mixer).

title: butterscotch lush
directions: Melt butter.
The mix flour and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until light golden brown.

title: stove top candied sweet potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in skillet on low heat.
Layer potatoes.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of white sugar, nutmeg and salt.
Add another layer of potatoes, sugar and brown sugar.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and salt. Cover and cook on medium heat about 10 minutes.
Turn with spatula and cook about 5 to 10 more minutes.
Remove potatoes to serving dish with spatula.
Cook liquid down to syrup stage and pour over potatoes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookies and bake with edges touching in ungreased pizza pan.
Cool.
Drain all fruit and save juice, except for strawberries.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix in large bowl until zucchini is coated.
Grease a 10 x 6-inch pan or 9-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake about 45 minutes, until top is golden brown.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Spread
can
rolls
in pan, pinching seams together. Blend cream
cheese,
sugar, vanilla and egg yolk thoroughly. Spread over
rolls
and top with other can of rolls, pinching seams together.
Brush
top
with
egg
white.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°, until brown.
Cool and refrigerate, then cut into squares.

title: apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place in layers in greased 9-inch or 10-inch square baking dish, apples, sugar and dry cake mix.
Pour melted margarine over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with pecans. Continue baking 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and add soup, tomato paste, salt, sugar, garlic powder and onion.
Let cook slowly while cooking the noodles. Drain noodles.
Mix together sour cream and cream cheese.
In a large casserole, place a layer of noodles; top with a layer of the meat sauce and a layer of the cheese mixture.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: party mix candy
directions: Melt first three ingredients.
In a large bowl mix all other ingredients together; add melted chocolate mixture.
Mix very well then add one box of powdered sugar.
Stir until all candy is coated.

title: pork chops and dirty rice
directions: Put raw rice in 2 quart casserole; brown pork chops and place on rice.
Put soup mix and water into pan with pork drippings; heat.
Pour over pork chops.
Cover and bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Have everything at room temperature.
Beat margarine.
Add sugar and beat again.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and milk.
Add flavoring.
Put in a 10-inch tube pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: double chocolate cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cookie crumbs and margarine or butter; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In medium saucepan, over medium heat, melt 1 cup chips with sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.
Pour evenly over prepared crust; top with nuts and remaining chips.
Bake 20 minutes or until set. Cool.
Chill, if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: pink panther salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in pan; brown and drain grease from sausage. Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with single layer of white bread slices.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and dry mustard together.
Pour over bread in pan.
Sprinkle browned sausage over eggs and bread.
Top with grated cheese.
Refrigerate
a couple of hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown beef in a 3 quart saucepan, drain off excess grease. Add sauce and water, simmer about 10 minutes.
In a bowl combine remaining ingredients except lasagna noodles, for the filling. Pour about 1 cup sauce in bottom of 13 x
9 x 2 inch baking pan. Layer 3
pieces of uncooked lasagna noodles over sauce (lasagna will expand to fill empty spaces).
Cover with about 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Spread 1/2 of the
cheese filling over sauce.
Repeat layers of lasagna, sauce and cheese filling.
Top with layer of lasagna noodles and remaining sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for
10 minutes longer.
Allow to stand about 10 minutes before cutting for easier handling,
8 or 10 servings.

title: potato corn soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onion and celery in small amount of water until it is done.
Add corn; heat to boiling.
Add milk and heat, but do not let milk boil.

title: quick and easy broccoli soup
directions: Prepare the cream of broccoli and Cheddar cheese soups as directed on the cans in a large saucepan.
When heated through, add the broccoli and the cheese.
When the cheese melts and the broccoli is at the tenderness you prefer, the soup is done.

title: pig picken cake(mandarin orange)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Stir in mandarin oranges. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: country cake
directions: In large bowl, beat sugar, oil and eggs at medium speed until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Blend in apples.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add gradually to mixture.
Stir in prunes and nuts. Spoon into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Check with toothpick.
Cool about 10 minutes. Invert pan while cooling.
Use funnel or wire rack.
Lightly dust cake with confectioners sugar.

title: sesame chicken brochettes
directions: Stir together soy sauce, sesame seed, preserves, sherry, oil, ginger and garlic in a medium bowl.
Cut chicken into about 30 pieces, about 3/4-inch square.
Cut green onions into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Add chicken and green onions to soy mixture.
Cover; refrigerate 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Soak 10 bamboo skewers in water.

title: funny faces(cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Blend in egg.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and stir until mixture is blended.
Chill dough 1 to 2 hours.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into shapes.
Decorate using M&M's, raisins, red hots.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for at least 30 minutes.
Fry in hot oil.

title: toffee apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice to soak apples in (to prevent them from turning dark while you chop).
Mix other ingredients; add to drained apples.

title: homemade hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together well.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add vanilla after removing from heat.

title: harvest bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour with 1/2 cup oats, 1/2 cup brown sugar and margarine.
Spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining oats, brown sugar, baking powder, vanilla, salt and pecans.
Spread over cereal mixture.
Bake 25 minutes longer.
Cool, then cut into bars.

title: milky way cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Melt candy over boiling water and add to mixture.
Bake in 3 layers at 350°
about 30 minutes.

title: peanut bar
directions: Sift flour and baking powder four times.
Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Make powdered sugar frosting and roll in crushed peanuts.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Cook ingredients after mixing well for 1 minute.
While stirring, add 6 1/2 cups sugar and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
After a boil that cannot be stirred down, boil for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove foam from top and stir for an additional 4 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal with wax or if you prefer lids.

title: larry's corn puddin'
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2-quart casserole with Pam.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients then pour into casserole. Bake covered for 1 hour.
Doubles well.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Form cheeses, onions and Worcestershire sauce into one large or two small balls.
Roll in nuts.
Make at least one day ahead.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Cook onion and garlic.
Add 2 cups of water and all ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: penuche fudge
directions: Butter a 9-inch square pan.
Combine sugars, cream, milk and butter in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until 238° on candy thermometer.
Cool to 110°.
Add vanilla. Beat until it loses gloss.
Add walnuts.
Pour into pan.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients (flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt).
Cut in shortening.
Add slightly beaten eggs, buttermilk and vanilla; beat for 2 minutes, then add the 1 cup boiling water. Don't beat.
Just mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured pans and bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
"Real moist cake".

title: summer salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: Slice strawberries and bananas. Add to spinach salad. Add sliced almonds. Drizzle with poppy seed dressing. Toss gently to coat. Refrigerate or serve.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix rice with soup and water in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 package onion soup.
Cover rice mixture with cut up chicken.
Top with remaining onion soup.
Cover pan tightly with Reynolds Wrap. Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 55 minutes in 350° oven.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: In skillet brown, ground beef.
Add picante sauce, soups and chili beans.
Line large casserole baking dish with tortilla chips.
Pour all ingredients over the chips.
Sprinkle grated cheese of choice (American or Cheddar) on top.
Heat in oven until cheese is melted.

title: nut milk
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Add water to thicken or dilute based on need.
Chill and serve.
You can substitute walnuts for cashews.
Remove brown shell by soaking in hot water.

title: spam casserole
directions: Cook green pepper and onion in	1
tablespoon margarine until tender.
In large casserole, mix
all ingredients.	Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: farmers breakfast casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp; add ham and onion. Cook and stir until onion is tender; drain. In a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half the bread cubes, potatoes and cheese. Top with all of the bacon mixture. Repeat layers of bread, potatoes and cheese. In a bowl, beat the eggs; add milk, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and pepper. Pour over all. Cover and chill overnight.

title: best ever slaw
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients; let stand.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring mixture to boil and pour cabbage while hot.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.
This will keep for a week or more in refrigerator.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon batter into skillet with small amount of melted butter or oil.
Flatten with a spatula.
Cook until golden brown on each side.
Serve with sour cream and dill or sour cream and chives.
Tomato sauce and grated Parmesan cheese is an alternative with less fat.

title: sweet pickled peaches
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar, and spices.
Bring to a boil. Drop in whole fresh peeled peaches.
Simmer peaches in syrup about 5 minutes.
Pack in hot, sterilized jars and pour syrup over the peaches.
Seal.
Yields 6 to 8 pints.

title: patty's applesauce cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Coat raisins and nuts (if wanted).
Cream shortening; add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add applesauce. Add to flour mixture and mix well.
Dissolve soda in water and add to mixture.
Mix well and pour in large greased and floured tube pan.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, eggs, evaporated milk and pumpkin spice together; set aside.
Pour into an oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry yellow cake mix on top of pie mixture.
Melt butter and pour over top of dry cake mix; spread evenly.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: cream cheese ice cream
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Beat in eggs, lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in light cream.
Freeze in 4 or 5-quart ice cream churn.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: mimi's salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite sized pieces.
Combine with radishes, tomatoes, cucumbers and onion.
Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar well. Pour over salad and toss well.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve chilled.

title: red or green pepper jelly(makes 6 to 7 pints)
directions: Wash dandelion blossoms and boil in water for 3 minutes. Strain, reserving 3 cups liquid.
Discard blossoms.
Combine reserved liquid, pectin and lemon extract in a large heavy saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until almost boiling; blend in sugar and bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour into sterilized 1/2-pint jars.
Seal at once with paraffin or cover and refrigerate to store.
Makes 5 half pints.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
When done, spread (while hot) with miniature marshmallows.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice.
Combine fruit, nuts and bananas in a large bowl.
Toss gently.
Combine pudding and pineapple juice.
Beat 1 minute at high speed.
Pour over fruit mixture and toss gently.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup with ground beef and simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix in sour cream until hot.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Sift powdered sugar.
Mix powdered sugar, margarine or butter, vanilla and peanut butter until well combined.
Form into 1-inch balls and chill for at least 3 hours.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together in top of double boiler.
Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate to coat.
I use a couple of toothpicks, then place on waxed paper to cool.

title: eleanor bain - pickles
directions: After cucumbers are soaked, wash and then soak in ice water for 3 hours.
Drain cucumbers.
Pour vinegar and sugar over cucumbers and boil for 30 minutes.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: carrot cake
directions: Put all ingredients in one bowl; mix well.
Place in slightly greased pan.
Bake at 400° until cake springs back lightly.
When cool, pour icing over cake.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Make pudding according to directions on the box.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Alternate pudding mix and bananas and cookies.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix together sugar, egg and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Mix lightly and add nut meats and let it raise in a baking pan 3/4 of an hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fast easy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top each piece with a slice of Swiss cheese. Arrange the sliced mushrooms over the cheese.
Mix the soup and the wine; pour over the chicken.
Sprinkle the stuffing mix over the top; drizzle on the melted butter.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until chicken is cooked through.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf(kid's favorite)
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese together well. Take half of the mixture and put in large greased loaf pan, leaving an indentation in the middle lengthwise.
Place cheese in the middle and put remaining meat mixture over top.
Make sure to seal the ends and sides so cheese won't drip out.
Spread about 3 tablespoons catsup on top of loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: oreo pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a baked pie shell. Freeze for 6 hours before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli. Beat eggs and add all ingredients. Put in casserole dish sprayed with Pam. Add Ritz cracker crumbs and pour melted margarine on top. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread slices and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brown and drain sausage.
Spoon sausage over bread crumbs.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Beat together the eggs, milk, salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour egg mixture over the bread, sausage and cheese.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cheese will rise to top during baking.
(Excellent for company breakfast.)

title: salami loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Form a roll 15-inches long.
Wrap in foil. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Unwrap and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: hot rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water. Add butter, sugar, eggs, salt and 4 cups flour. Stir and then beat until smooth, about 1 minute. Stir in the remaining flour, working the last 2 cups in by hand. This dough will be very soft. Cover tightly and store in refrigerator overnight or until needed. Bake in 400° oven 15 to 20 minutes. Turn out on a wire rack. One third of this dough makes 12 pan rolls.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together and put in casserole with melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until set.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion in large skillet.
Add all other ingredients, except cornbread batter.
Spoon the batter over top of mix.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Brown sausage in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Remove and place on paper towels, leaving drippings in Dutch oven.
Brown chicken in drippings and remove to paper towel.
Reserve drippings.
Measure drippings and add enough oil to make 1/2 cup. Heat and add flour to hot oil; cook, stirring constantly, until roux is chocolate colored, but not burned (about 30 minutes).
Add onions, green pepper and celery.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Gradually stir in hot water; bring to boil.
Return chicken breasts to Dutch oven; add garlic and other 5 ingredients. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 hour.
Remove chicken breasts; cool.
Return sausage to Dutch oven and cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Stir in green onions and simmer 30 more minutes.
Add salt.
Bone chicken and cut in strips.
Add to gumbo.
Heat thoroughly.
Remove bay leaves.
Serve gumbo over cooked rice. Serves 8.
Serve with green salad and garlic bread.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Blend dry ingredients, then cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Add liquid ingredients and toss with fork.
Chill before rolling.
Divide in 6 equal parts.
Can be frozen and used as needed.
Makes 3 double crust pies.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar, then add eggs, then everything else.
Roll in balls.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Add all ingredients, enough salad dressing to mix. Chill at least 1 hour.

title: pork chop casserole 2
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper and put in baking dish. Top with tater tots.
Mix 2 cans of soup and water.
You may not need all of the 1/4 cup of water.
You want the soup thinned out but not runny.
Pour on top of tater tots.
Bake at 400 degrees for 45-60 minutes.
Top with cheese and cook until cheese is melted.

title: tea donuts
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder and spices.
Beat in egg, sugar and oleo.
Add flour and milk.
Beat.
Fold in vanilla and lemon rind.
Drop by teaspoon into hot grease; fry until brown.

title: lisa's no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter until blended.
Heat to boiling; cook for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Let cool, then refrigerate.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Parboil about 1 hour.
Drain off liquid and pour boiling water over beans.
Put in bean pot.
Add all ingredients and cover with hot water.
Bake in slow oven (250° to 275°) all day.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut sugar cookies in 1/8-inch slices.
Place on cookie sheet overlapping to form crust.
Bake according to directions on package.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and spread over cookies.
Place fruit over entire surface.
Mix water and marmalade and spread over top of pizza.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Slice just like a pizza slice.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk; stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in 1/2 container of Cool Whip.
Add bananas.
Layer with vanilla wafers.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.

title: sausage and cheddar quiche
directions: Bake pie shell at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Add mushrooms, onion, green pepper, parsley, basil, garlic and salt; mix well.
Spoon into pie shell.
Top with cheese.
Combine milk, eggs and cornstarch in bowl; beat until foamy.
Pour evenly over cheese. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Lightly brown meat and onion.
Cook until just tender; add seasoning, beans and soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat casserole mixture until bubbling.
Pour into casserole.
Top hot mixture with baking powder biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: meatless holuptsi
directions: Cook rice until soft.
Add grated potatoes and onion to rice. Mix well.
Parboil cabbage head.
Let steam until soft enough to work with.
Cut out core and separate leaves.
Put rice mixture in cabbage leaf.
Roll up tucking in ends as you roll.
Place in shallow pot or Dutch oven.
Cover with any leftover leaves.
Add tomato sauce or tomato soup.
Cook on medium heat about 1 hour or more until cabbage is done.

title: meat filled manicotti
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
Cool in single layer on foil.
Heat oven at 350°.

title: hershey pie
directions: In medium microwave bowl, place chocolate pieces, milk and marshmallows.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Stir well and microwave on High for another 30 seconds to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds until chocolate and marshmallows are melted and mixture is smooth.
Cool completely.

title: microwave pudding
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl and microwave on Normal for 12 minutes, stirring with whisk every 3 minutes.
Stir well after the 12 minutes.
Let stand until cool. Chocolate may be added, blueberries, pineapple, etc.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved. Add cream cheese; stir until mixture is thoroughly combined. Cool.
Fold in apples, nuts and whipped topping.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.
Yields 9 to 12 servings.

title: date roll
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to boil and cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Beat until creamy.
Pour onto linen towel wrung out of cold water.
Roll.
When solid, unroll and slice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar and butter together.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk or sour cream and dry ingredients to batter.
Fold in mashed bananas and pecans.
Pour in a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: lemonade
directions: Strain the lemon juice and add the syrup, water and salt. Fill tall glasses about 2/3 full of ice.
Pour th fruit juice over the ice and serve immediately.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix all together.
Chill 2 hours before serving.
Serve with apple slices.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Beat with mixer the peanut butter and margarine, gradually adding sugar.
Mix in Rice Krispies with a spoon.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Coat with melted chocolate.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on.
Cool.
Peel skin and grate potatoes.
In saucepan, melt margarine and cheese.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 1/2 cups sour cream, 1/3 cup chopped onion, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Put potatoes in buttered dish.
Add other ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato fruit salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
In a small bowl, mix together, the next 4 ingredients.
Add to fruit and potato mixture.
Add more sour cream if mixture is too dry.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill.
Mound on lettuce leaves or serve on a platter.

title: rolls
directions: Pour scalded milk into mixing bowls, add honey, butter, beaten egg and dry yeast.
Add flour and beat; knead in the rest of the flour that cannot be beaten in.
Place in greased bowl, set in warm place until double in size (about 1 hour, 20 minutes).
Shape into rolls; let rise again until doubled.
Bake in 375° oven about 20 minutes.

title: tasty barbecues(double for more than 4 people)
directions: Fry onions and meat until meat crumbles.
Stir remaining ingredients in a bowl and add to meat mixture.
Simmer until thick.

title: low calorie egg custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine egg, egg whites, Splenda, milk and vanilla extract.

With wire whisk, beat until smooth and well blended, approximately 1 minute. Pour mixture into four 6-ounce custard cups. Arrange cups in a large baking pan so they do not touch. Pour very hot water, not boiling, into the pan so the water is 1-inch deep. Place pan in middle of oven. Bake custard 40 minutes or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean. Transfer cups from pan to wire rack. Cool to room temperature. Chill in refrigerator for at least two hours.

title: cream of crab soup caroline
directions: In saucepan, combine onion, butter, flour and chicken bouillon cube; saute until onion is clear.
Add water and crabmeat; bring to simmer.
Add half and half and remaining ingredients.
Bring to scalding temperature.
Do not boil.
Serve with pat of butter and garnish.

title: honey-glazed chicken breasts
directions: To reduce fat and cholesterol, remove all skin and fat from chicken breasts prior to cooking.

title: strawberry chiffon squares
directions: In small saucepan melt margarine; stir in wafer crumbs.
Pat firmly on bottom of 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Chill.
In large bowl dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in sweetened milk and undrained strawberries.
Fold in marshmallows and whipped cream. Pour in pan.
Chill 2 hours until set.
If desired garnish with whipped topping and strawberries.

title: kraut salad relish
directions: Toss ingredients together.
Cover and chill 4 to 12 hours. Toss again and drain before serving.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, brown chicken in shortening.
Remove and set aside.
Stir flour in until very brown, making a roux.
Add onion, celery and garlic; cook until slightly wilted.
Gradually add hot water until roux is well blended.
Add chicken and seasonings (except gumbo file).
Cover with a tight-fitting lid and bring to steaming point.
Lower heat and cook until chicken is tender, about 2 hours.
Add parsley 5 minutes before removing from heat.
Add gumbo file.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: confetti bubble ring(bread)
directions: Fry bacon crisp; break into pieces.
Combine with cheese, pepper and onions in large bowl.
Cut biscuits into quarters; add to bacon mixture.
Pour melted margarine over the whole mixture and knead together with
hands.
Turn into a greased tube pan. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Invert onto platter and cut into wedges.

title: perfect meringue
directions: Mix the cornstarch and 2 tablespoons sugar with the water. Cook together until clear; set aside.
Add a bit of salt (1/4 teaspoon) to the egg whites; whip until foamy or standing in peaks.
Add the sugar mixture; continue beating until creamy.
Add the 6 tablespoons sugar gradually, beating until very creamy. Pile on pie.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°, or until golden brown.

title: sausage brunch
directions: Fry sausage; crumble and drain well on paper towels.
Beat eggs slightly; add all other ingredients and mix well.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.
Serve with fresh fruit and Danish pastries, it makes a delicious breakfast or brunch.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together thoroughly.
Put in large covered casserole. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: new orleans school of cooking gumbo(yield: 15 to 20 servings)
directions: In large skillet, brown flour and oil until dark brown (Hershey's chocolate color) over medium-high heat, stirring continuously.
Do not burn!
Add trinity (this is the onion, celery and pepper) and stir continuously until vegetables are tender.
Add garlic at very end.
Gradually stir in liquid and bring to boil. Add chicken and sausage and simmer 1 hour or more (the longer, the better).
About 10 minutes before serving, add green onions.
Serve over rice, if desired.

title: party mix
directions: Mix all cereals and nuts together.
Mix oleo, salt and sauce. Heat until oleo melts.
Pour over mixture; mix well.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours.
Stir every 20 minutes.
Use the largest pan you can that will fit in your oven so it will not be so thick.

title: marshmallow torte
directions: Melt the marshmallows and milk; let cool.
Add the Cool Whip and berries.
Put in baked crust.
Refrigerate.

title: crab meltaways
directions: Cut muffins in half, making 12 pieces.
Mix all other ingredients.
Spread on muffins; put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Freeze until ready to use.
You can cut each half into fourths when using as finger foods for a party.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Cook together until thickened, apple juice, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Stir apples into mixture and pour into pie shell. Sprinkle top crust with water and nutmeg.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Mix and beat 4 minutes.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ground beef and pepper skillet
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion until onion is tender.
Drain. Season with pepper.
Stir in gravy, add green pepper and pea pods. Simmer uncovered until pea pods and green pepper are just tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 6.

title: salted peanut crisps
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Stir flour, soda, and salt together and add to margarine mixture.
Mix in peanuts and refrigerate dough.
Roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: beef porcupine balls
directions: Mix rice and beef together.
Add beaten egg.
Shape into small meat balls and brown in skillet.
Combine beef seasoning packet (from rice mix) and 2 1/2 cups hot water in pan.
Pour over meat balls.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Thicken gravy as desired.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly, then refrigerate until chilled.

title: christmas scent
directions: Combine all ingredients in tea kettle or saucepan and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer as long as desired. Check often and add additional water, if needed. Mixture may be stored in refrigerator for several days and reused. Yield: 4 cups.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Scoop onto greased cookie sheet using a 1/4 measuring cup per cookie.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato corn chowder
directions: With a sharp knife, cut corn off cob, leaving kernel bases attached, with back of knife.
Scrape cob to extract the creamy pulp (reserve).

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Place chicken cubes in oiled shallow baking pan.
Top with a dressing made of remaining ingredients.
This can be done the day before the dish is to be served.
Make a thin gravy of 4 tablespoons chicken fat, 6 tablespoons flour and 1 quart chicken broth.
Season to taste.
Pour this hot mixture over dressing and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: microwave stuffed peppers
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients and fill in pepper halves.
Pour sauce over peppers and cook on High for 25 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: soda cracker fudge
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, peanut butter and vanilla together; set aside.
In medium saucepan, mix together granulated sugar, butter or margarine and milk; bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour over cracker mixture.
Mix well and pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: sesame chicken nuggets
directions: In a small bowl, mix all ingredients together except the chicken.
Add the chicken and coat evenly.
Spread the chicken out on a broiling pan.
Broil for 10 minutes or until lightly browned, turning once.
Serve with barbecue sauce or stuff into a pita pocket with lettuce and tomato.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients in crock-pot.

title: string beans and corn
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; set aside bacon.
Save drippings.
Boil water.
Add sugar, salt and string beans; cook about 10 minutes. Add corn and bacon drippings; mix.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes longer, or until beans are tender.
Drain and serve (with bacon, if desired).

title: oriental-style orange slaw
directions: In a bowl, toss together shredded cabbage, oranges, water chestnuts and onions.
Reserve broth packet from soup mix for another use.
Crumble noodles into salad.
Pour enough Sweet and Sour Dressing over mixture to moisten, toss well to coat with dressing.
Cover and chill 30 minutes or more before serving to allow flavors to blend. Makes 8 servings each with 96 calories, 2g. fat and 0 mg. cholesterol.

title: rump roast
directions: Put pats of butter, meat tenderizer, 1/4 cup oil and dry red wine over roast.
Sprinkle rosemary, garlic cloves, salt and pepper.
Add cut potatoes into pan, cut lengthwise.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Take out potatoes and continue cooking meat until done as desired.

title: miss maggie's fruiti fruiti sherbet
directions: Mix gelatin with cold water
to soften.
Add sugar to 1 cup boiling water, boil 5
minutes.
Add gelatin to hot syrup. Cool. Add salt, lemon juice and orange juice to syrup.
Cool. Add pineapple,	cherries
and
mashed
bananas.
Prepare
egg whites and white corn syrup.
Fold
in fruit mixture.
Pour in ice cream freezer.
Freeze as you would any ice cream.

title: orange jello pie
directions: Mix jello and let cool.
Add chilled milk.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: crisp crusted baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry; set aside.
Beat egg and milk in a bowl.
In another bowl mix potato flakes, garlic powder and Parmesan cheese.
Melt butter or margarine in a shallow baking pan.
Roll coated chicken pieces in the butter or margarine and place them skin side up in the pan.
Bake at 400°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix together and bake in a greased pie pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut up chicken and place on bottom of baking dish.
Combine cream of chicken soup, milk and water.
Pour over chicken.
Place biscuits on top of mixture.
Bake at 400° until biscuits are browned.

title: sugar-free hot spiced fall or holiday drink
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine first four ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Remove spices and orange slices.
Stir in Equal.
Serve hot or cold.
Diabetic Exchange:
3 fruits.

title: sweet potato bread pudding
directions: Beat milk, sugar, eggs, cinnamon, allspice and vanilla together.
Mix bread crumbs until soft.
Add sweet potatoes; mix well, then add nuts, coconut and raisins.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Cook in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add 1/4 cup of mixture to 6 ounces of boiling water.
Yields 50 (1-cup) servings.
Great for camping.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets.
Reserve 3 cups of beet juice.
Add vinegar, salt, sugar, mustard seed, allspice, cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Bring to a boil, simmer 20 minutes.
Remove cloves and cinnamon sticks. Pour over beets in sterilized jars.
Process in water bath 30 minutes.
Yields 7 pints.

title: texas rum cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, pudding, eggs, rum, water and oil for 2 minutes.
Pour into tube pan, greased and lined with the pecan halves.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool cake for 5 minutes, then pour glaze over it.

title: chocolate chip rocky road pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, soda and salt in bowl. In another bowl, cream butter and sugars until blended.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Mix in dry ingredients, along with chocolate chips and nuts.
Pat into 14-inch round pizza pan that has been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Bake 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle topping over cookie crust.
Let stand 5 minutes, then swirl with spatula.
Cool completely.
Cut into wedges before serving.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring to boil, vinegar, oil and sugar.
Let cool.
Mix all together.
Chill.
Gets better with age.
Good for several weeks.

title: lady baltimore cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, shortening, 1/2 cup milk and vanilla. Mix in large bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Add remaining 3/4 cup milk and 5 egg whites.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press lightly to see if center springs back.
If it doesn't, bake 5 minutes longer.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries, orange and apples through food chopper on medium disc.
Save
juice.
Dissolve
jello
and gelatin in hot water.
Dissolve
plain
gelatin
in
a
little cold water before adding to
the
hot
water.
Mix fruits, jello mixture, saved juice, sugar
and
pineapple all together and stir well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until needed.
Cut in squares and serve with your favorite salad dressing.

title: coconut drops
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Spread coconut on cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes stirring occasionally until lightly toasted, cool.
With a mixer on medium speed, beat butter, sugar, eggs, baking powder, vanilla, baking soda and salt until creamy.
Stir in flour, in 3 additions, alternating with sour cream.
Fold in 1 cup toasted coconut.
Drop level tablespoons 1 1/2 inches apart on baking sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are a pale brown.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: beefy noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions, drain and set aside.
Saute mushrooms, celery, onion, and green pepper in butter in a large Dutch oven until tender.
Add beef, cook until browned, stirring occasionally.
Drain, stir in next 8 ingredients (dried oregano, salt
pepper, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, chopped tomatoes, creamed style corn and tomato soup).
Add noodles, spoon mixture into a greased deep 3 quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake uncovered 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: bread pudding cake
