directions: Cut bread into small cubes.
Soak in milk.
Stir and mix well, making as smooth as possible.
Beat eggs and add to above mixture. Add remainder of ingredients and mix well.
Place in greased 9 x 12-inch pan and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: maple-nut cake
directions: Blend all cake ingredients, except nuts; blend until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed; fold in nuts.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool 25 minutes.

title: saucy chicken and asparagus
directions: If desired, partially cook asparagus.
Drain.
Place the asparagus in a greased 9-inch square baking dish.
In a skillet over medium heat, brown the chicken in oil on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Arrange chicken over asparagus.
In a bowl, mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until the chicken is tender and juices run clear.
Sprinkle with cheese. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; add cranberry sauce.
Mix well.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Put in large baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top and add potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except lettuce and tomatoes.
Chill. Pour over lettuce and tomato wedges at serving time.

title: perfect cheese cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and pat into bottom of spring-form pan.

title: nine layered salad
directions: Add in large bowl in order listed. Refrigerate 8 to 24 hours before serving. Toss just before serving.

title: country chicken soup
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot, except noodles, in order listed.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or high 4 to 6 hours.
One hour before serving, remove chicken and debone. Return to crock-pot and add noodles.
Turn to high, cover and cook 1 hour.
May thicken with cornstarch and water.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix as any other cake, except dissolve baking powder in just a small amount of the milk and add last.
Start in cold oven and cook at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and chopped pecans and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown; cool.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Blend in oil and set aside. Dissolve baking soda in boiling water. Stir in corn syrup and molasses.
Let the mixture cool. Add egg.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup flour mixture into unbaked pastry shell.
Carefully cover with liquid filling.
Top with remaining flour mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until pie sets.

title: egg souffle
directions: Layer bread and cheese in glass baking dish (ending with cheese).
Mix eggs, mustard, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over layered bread and cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Prepare and refrigerate overnight.

title: frozen fruity bars
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water. Pour into paper or plastic cups, freeze until almost firm.
Insert wooden stick into each cup.
Freeze about 8 hours or overnight.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Boil sausage and chicken until chicken is tender.
Cook rice as box directs, but only half the time suggested.
Add chicken, sausage, onions and hot sauce to rice.
Stir.
Cover and cook an additional 15 to 20 minutes, over low heat, stirring occasionally. If desired, add extra seasoning to taste.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, cream the peanut butter, shortening and brown sugar.
Add the egg, vanilla and salt, beating well. Combine flour and soda. Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart on baking sheet.
You may flatten slightly with crisscross tines of a fork.

title: taffy
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and stir until dissolved.
Boil until the mixture forms a hard ball in cold water.
When mixture cools to very warm, pull the candy until it becomes too hard to pull.
Cut into pieces.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Thaw frozen peas; tear lettuce in chunks and place in large bowl.
Add in layers, celery, green pepper, onion and peas. Spread over with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle sugar, cheese and crumbled bacon on the mixture.
Cover with plastic and chill for at least 8 hours.
(Other ingredients can be used if desired:
cauliflower, cucumbers and mushrooms.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients while broccoli cooks.
Drain broccoli. Place broccoli in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Pour mixture over top.
Then crumble Ritz crackers over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked flounder
directions: Make sure flounder is fresh and clean.
Wet flounder with water and lightly roll in bread crumbs.
Place each piece of flounder on foil-covered cookie sheet.
Place a small pat of margarine in center of each piece of flounder.
Sprinkle lightly with lemon juice.
Bake in a 350° oven until flaky.
Do not overcook or edges will be hard.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, soup and cheese.
Pour in pan and top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make a batch of your favorite brownies.
Let cool, then layer brownies, chocolate Cool Whip, pudding that has been prepared according to directions on box, crushed candy bars and white Cool Whip.
Continue layering.
Should have about 3 layers.
Sprinkle top with a few crushed candy bars.

title: tomato soup
directions: Mix melted butter, flour, sugar and salt.
Add a little hot juice to mixture, then
mix in with boiling juice and boil 1/2 hour.
Put in jars and
cold pack 30 minutes.
Add milk or water and heat before serving.
Yields 4 quarts.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: inside out ravioli
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown ground meat and chopped onion in oil.
Cook spinach.
Drain; save liquid and add water to make 1 cup.
Set aside.

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice around pork chops.
Mix tomato juice, chili powder and garlic powder and pour over pork chops and rice, making sure rice is covered with juice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add meat and marinate for 24 hours.
Place in food dehydrator or oven until chewy, not brittle.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Dissolve coffee in 2 cups water; bring just to a boil.
Add both mixtures together; cool overnight. Add vodka and vanilla.
Let sit at least 2 weeks, the longer it sits the better.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix dry cake mix and the margarine together until crumbly. Press into 9 x 12-inch greased baking pan.
Add 3 egg yolks with 1 pint of sour cream.
Add 1/3 cup sugar.
Pour this on top of cake mixture.
Add 1 large can sliced, drained peaches on top of sour cream mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until the custard is firm in the center.

title: bailey's irish creme
directions: Mix in a blender.
Serve over ice.

title: squash and apple bake(delicious)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut peeled squash into 1/2-inch pieces and arrange in an ungreased casserole.
Top with sliced apples.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over top of apples.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour.

title: mary's pineapple cake(3 layers)
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Beat mixture after adding each egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake.

title: pork 'n beans
directions: Fry bacon and medium onion.
Drain little grease and fry onion in tablespoon butter.
Add ingredients and beans.
Simmer.

title: nibble mix
directions: Place butter
in
a baking dish; stir in Worcestershire sauce. Add dry cereals, pretzels and nuts.
Sprinkle with the garlic and onion.
Mix
well.	Bake
at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: mexican lunch
directions: Cook sausage until almost done.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes, milk and macaroni.
Mix these, then add sour cream along with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Bake at 350° until mixture bubbles real good.
Top with grated cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Melt cheese.
(You can leave cheese and bread crumbs off, if you want to.)

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in bowl and beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add apples and nuts.
Use spoon to mix.
Put in square or tube pan (well-greased).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until well done.
If using tube pan, bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour icing over hot cake.

title: lime punch
directions: Dissolve jello and
sugar in hot water.
Add cold water, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; slowly beat in sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat briskly.
Blend entire mixture.
Pour into pastry lined pie tin.
Bake 10 minutes in 450° oven; reduce heat to 350° and bake until custard sets, about 30 minutes.
Serve plain or with sweetened whipped cream.
Add pecan halves over top of pie.

title: lime-pineapple parfait pie
directions: Heat pineapple juice to boiling in a 2-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add vanilla ice cream to hot liquid.
Stir immediately until melted.
Chill, until mixture is thickened, but not set, 20 to 25 minutes.
Fold in drained pineapple.
Turn into cooled, baked 9-inch pie shell. Chill until firm, at least 2 hours.

title: wienerschnitzel
directions: Season veal cutlets; dip in flour.
Next dip in beaten egg and last in bread crumbs (both sides).
Fry on each side 5 to 6 minutes in hot shortening.
Garnish with lemon slices (optional).

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Add last 5 ingredients to sauteed onion.
Stir and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spicy hot chocolate
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, unsweetened chocolate, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in water.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until chocolate melts.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk; heat over low heat until mixture is hot.
Beat with rotary beater until foamy. Serve in mugs or cups.
Garnish with whipped dessert topping. Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream twists
directions: Dissolve yeast in water with some of the sugar.
Combine all dry ingredients and then the remaining.
Knead several times on floured board until smooth.
Roll into a rectangle 24 x 6-inch.

title: butterscotch haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch pieces in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Add peanuts and noodles; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Store candy in cool place.

title: cheese spread
directions: Heat oven to 300°, then turn off.
Soften Velveeta and cream cheese in oven.
Mix cheeses, margarine and sandwich spread with mixer.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, salt, lemon rind, flour and cornmeal thoroughly.
Beat eggs with spiral eggbeater thoroughly. Add melted butter, lemon juice and milk; mix well.
Pour into pie crust (unbaked).
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until set.

title: hot or cold crab dip
directions: Bake at 325° until bubbles.

title: chicken dish
directions: Flour chicken and brown in casserole dish.
Put 1 cup uncooked rice; place chicken on top of rice.
Pour Lipton onion soup over that and pour 2 cups over that.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the cheese, together and pour 1/2 of the batter in 9-inch iron skillet and cover with 1/2 of the cheese.
Pour remaining batter on the cheese and top this with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until done.
Serves 6.

title: holiday dessert
directions: Dissolve lemon jello with 1/2 amount of water called for but not set (slightly jelled).
Whip cream.
Cream the cheese and add the pineapple.
Fold this mixture into the whipped cream and add the cooled lemon jello.
Pour into a 14 x 10 x 2-inch pan and put into refrigerator to set.
Dissolve the cherry jello with 1 cup boiling water and 1 cup cold water and chill.
When cool, but not jelled pour over the other mixture as an icing.
Leave in the refrigerator until ready to serve (at least 4 hours).

title: cheese dip
directions: Cut Jiffy Jack into small cubes and combine with tomatoes and green chiles.
Heat in microwave oven or slow cooker until cheese is melted.
Serve with chips.

title: german baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° to 375° for 40 minutes.
Uncover last 10 minutes to brown.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite sized pieces; fry with salt, pepper and onion until crisp and tender.
Cook broccoli in boiling water, salted, and drain.
Combine cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Combine chicken, broccoli and soup mixture.
Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs and 3/4 cup grated cheese on top.
Heat at 350° until hot.

title: hot salsa
directions: In skillet with just enough oil to keep from sticking, place peppers (whole) and chop onion.
Cool on low until tender.
Slice peppers.
Mix all ingredients and serve with corn chips.
The thin restaurant style chips are the best.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean peppers.
Steam in covered pan for 5 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients using only 1/2 can of the tomato soup.
Mix well.
Stuff peppers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Pour remaining 1/2 can of tomato soup over peppers and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, layer tortilla shells.
Cover bottom and sides of dish with shells and set aside.

title: marinated green bean salad
directions: Heat sugar, oil and vinegar until sugar is dissolved, stirring frequently.
Cool.
Pour beans, peas, pimento, celery, onion and pepper into sugar mixture; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: whole strawberries with french cream
directions: Beat cream until stiff.
Fold in sugar, sour cream and peel. Serve over strawberries.
Sprinkle with grated chocolate.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mom's piggies
directions: Core
and
boil
cabbage heads, removing leaves as they fall off,
until all are gone.
Let cool.
Combine beef, rice, chicken and
rice
soup,
can tomato soup, salt and pepper. Make piggies;
wrap
in	cabbage.
Place
a
layer
of cabbage leaves on	bottom of roaster to prevent piggies from sticking. Line piggies up in roaster; cover them with sauerkraut, tomato soup and 2 cans water.
Cover and cook in a 375° oven.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Layer asparagus, peas, cheese and water chestnuts.
Combine mushroom soup and seasonings.
Pour over vegetables.
Melt 1 stick of butter.
Cut 4 slices of bread into strips and put in butter.
Place strips on top of casserole, then cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves a bunch.

title: no bake orange nut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Shape into small balls and roll in coconut, confectioners sugar or melted chocolate.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute until crisp the bacon and onion.
Add garlic powder. In warm crock-pot, put mustard, vinegar and brown sugar.
Add pork and beans.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 2 to 3 hours, or more.

title: california chicken
directions: Put oil and lemon juice in skillet and add all spices and salt.
Bring this to a boil.
Add chicken and turn heat down and saute until tender.
Let most of the water cook out and brown the tender chicken a little.

title: cocoa puff cookies
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients about 30 seconds.
Remove from fire and add peanut butter and Cocoa Puffs.
Mix well until Puffs are coated and spoon out on waxed paper.

title: mullet amandine
directions: Place fillets in baking dish, skin side down.
Sprinkle with lemon
juice
and butter.
Add almonds and bake 15 to 20 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Blend all together.
Knead until dough consistency.
Roll out thin; spread with peanut butter.
Cut across.
Roll into roll; cut in pieces.
Let stand until set.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large bowl.
Shape into small balls (1 1/2-inch round) and freeze on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield:
About 60.

title: mama o's macaroni pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Drain water from cooked macaroni and mix in butter, salt and pepper. Pour half macaroni in 2-quart casserole dish; spread evenly. Sprinkle layer of grated cheese, using half cheese.
Repeat layer of macaroni and layer of cheese.
Add milk to beaten egg and pour over macaroni and cheese layers.
Place pats of butter around on top of mixture.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake for about 30 minutes.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Cut pound cake horizontally into three layers.
Sprinkle orange juice over cake layers.
Then cut cake into 1-inch cubes. Prepare pudding mix as directed on package.
Layer half the cake cubes, pudding, strawberries and Cool Whip.
Repeat layers. Really pretty fixed in a deep glass bowl.
Fix day ahead.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Reserve 1 cup of chicken broth. Combine soups, green chilies, spices and chicken broth over low heat until well blended.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover bottom of 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole dish with 2 cups of corn chips.
Spread 1/2 the chicken over this layer, then 1/2 the sauce and 1/2 of the cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken curry
directions: Layer peas and chicken.
Combine and mix soup, mayonnaise, mushrooms, curry powder and cheese.
Pour over chicken and peas. Top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or so.
Serve with rice, Chinese noodles or plain.
Can be frozen.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Shape into walnut size balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: souper chicken(easy)
directions: Place chicken pieces in foil-lined sheet cake pan.
Spoon soup over chicken pieces and spread; cover with foil.
Place in oven; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until chicken is no longer pink.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then beat in eggs and oil.
Add carrots and nuts.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch round pans.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Frost top and sides with at least 2 1/2 cups of favorite frosting.

title: homemade graham nuts
directions: This cereal has a great crunchy texture and is a bit sweeter than Grape Nuts.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate until firm.
Form into ball and roll in crushed nuts (peanuts, pecans or almonds).

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain well.
Mix other ingredients. Heat in saucepan.
Pour over carrots, green pepper and onion. Let sit in refrigerator for 10 to 12 hours.

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel onions and slice thin.
Brown lightly in butter.
Add bouillon and simmer for 30 minutes.
Spoon into bowls.
Add bread. Put Swiss cheese on top and put under broiler until cheese melts.

title: miss ruth's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: no sugar pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sweetener, syrup and margarine together.
Put pecans on bottom of pie crust.
Gently add pie mixture without stirring. Bake at 325° until set, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: old fashioned chew bread
directions: Combine sugar & eggs in heavy pan.
Stirring well.
Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
(Be careful, scorching will occur easily.)
Remove from heat add all other ingredients.
Place in greased, floured oblong pan.
Bake in 15x10-inch pan, at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Put oil, zucchini, eggs and vanilla in blender.
Blend thoroughly, then put in a large mixing bowl.
Beat sugar into blended mixture, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour in a loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix pumpkin, eggs and milk from the directions on the side of the can.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle yellow cake mix over it.
Pour 2 sticks of melted butter over entire cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with 1 cup sugar.
Put margarine in a 2-quart casserole, melt in oven (325°).
Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour over melted margarine.
Do not stir!
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix first 9 ingredients.
Pour into large 11 x 15 pan and bake for 25-30 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: cheese grits
directions: Bring water and salt to a rolling boil and stir in grits. Cook at high heat for about 3 minutes and add a stick or less of butter as desired.
Cut heat and stir in about 1 1/2 cups cheese, more if desired.
Cook on very low heat until well mixed and cheese completely melts.
Stir occasionally as it is cooking on low heat.

title: pralines
directions: Brown 1 cup sugar in skillet slowly.
Bring to a boil the remaining 2 cups sugar, salt and milk.
Boil 2 or 3 minutes.
Add caramelized sugar and boil to soft ball stage.
(Test in cold water.)

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Mix soda with buttermilk.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour.
Mix well.
Add salt and vanilla and almond extracts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan in cold oven at 325°
for 1 1/4 hours or 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Allow to cool a few minutes before removing from pan.

title: baked pork tenderloin
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients.
Marinate pork 6 hours or overnight. Bake 1 hour at 325° or until tender.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and break broccoli into small pieces.
Toss with onion, broken-up bacon and shredded cheese.
Combine sugar, salad dressing and vinegar and add to mixture.
Chill.

title: quick quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Press pie crust into quiche dish.
Add shredded cheese and desired fillings in a separate bowl.
Beat eggs; add half and half.
Mix together.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Reduce to 325° for another 15 minutes.

title: stuffed shells with three fillings
directions: Prepare Marinara Sauce and cook, uncovered, while preparing fillings.
Prepare fillings, one at a time, and set aside until all are ready.
Cook shells according to package directions; drain and rinse in cold water and drain again.
Divide into thirds and stuff.
Butter or spray several pans to hold all the shells.
Pour the Marinara Sauce, then the Balsamella Sauce over the shells in each pan and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until sauce bubbles and pasta is heated through (can be frozen).
Yields 12 to 24 servings.

title: rich frosted brownies
directions: Combine sugar, flour, eggs, butter, cocoa and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in nuts. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until center is firm.
Cool.
Frost with Chocolate Frosting.

title: date nut bars(here is another good date recipe.)
directions: Mix each ingredient, one at a time, in a large bowl.
Pour into an oblong pan, lightly greased and floured.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut while still warm.

title: make ahead eggs benedict
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, arrange muffins, cut side up.
Place 2 bacon slices on each muffin half.
Half fill 10-inch skillet with water.
Bring just to boiling.
Break one egg into a dish. Carefully slide egg into water.
Repeat with 3 more eggs. Simmer, uncovered, 3 minutes or until set.
Remove eggs with a slotted spoon.
Repeat with remaining eggs.
Place 1 egg on top of each muffin stack.
Set aside.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls in deep oil and fry until brown.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Blend the first 2 ingredients together with a mixer; then add last 2 ingredients and blend.
Dip whole berries into mix.
Great for any get together!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel, cook and mash potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Place in greased baking dish.

title: rice with beans
directions: Put the oil in the pot and then all the ingredients.
Then add the beans, water and last, the rice.
Wait until it dries.

title: round steak roll-up
directions: In an electric skillet, brown steak whole.
Cool.
Spread prepared dressing on steak.
Roll up; use toothpicks to hold together.
Place in foil; pour mushroom soup and milk over steak. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each egg is added. Add alternately flour and milk. Mix well. Stir in extract. Mix until blended. Stir in coconut. Pour into a greased and floured pan. Bake in 325° oven for 75 to 90 minutes.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together until fluffy the shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill 1 hour. Roll, cut and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix ingredients with apples.
Pour into pie shell.
Dot butter on top.
Put
other
pie
shell
on top and make slits. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400° until light golden brown.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Blend milk, lemon juice, lemon peel and egg yolks until thoroughly blended.
Pour into pie crust.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and margarine.
Add sugar, gradually creaming well, then add flour alternately with eggs.
Put in large, greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Place in cold oven; turn oven to 300°.
Bake one hour and 45 minutes.
Let stand in pan for 30 minutes to cool before taking up.

title: lucky lemon
directions: Beat pudding with milk.
Spread over previous layer.
Spread cool whip on top.
Chill before serving.

title: tom's cheese ball
directions: Cream cheeses and butter.
Add rest of ingredients, except walnuts, and mix.
Line a small bowl with plastic wrap.
Put mixture into bowl; cover and refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Take chilled mixture out; form balls.
Roll in nuts.
Add more chives, if desired.
Serve at room temperature.

title: chicken cheese casserole
directions: Bake chicken breasts in foil, wrapped tight, at 300° for 1 hour.
Shred into bite size pieces.
Mix in bowl the soups, milk, onion and green chile salsa.
Layer tortillas, soup mix, cheese and chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape in loaf pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mash cheese with cherry juice; add cut up cherries.
Drain pineapple and add marshmallows.
Mix well.
Fold in sweetened whipped cream.
Add nuts and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: "ironed" sandwiches
directions: You will need foil and an iron.

title: edible play dough
directions: Wash your hands.
Mix well with your hands and play.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place stuffing mix in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish.
Place chicken on top of this. Pour soup and water over this. Bake 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: frozen peach beach cooler
directions: Mix all ingredients into blender and puree until smooth.
Pour into glasses.
Serves 4.

title: fried whole baby okra
directions: Wash thoroughly.
Cut off stem end and tip of okra pods.
Cook in boiling, salted water for 8 minutes.
Drain and dry completely. Roll in seasoned cornmeal.
Fry in deep fat.
Serve with sliced pork and fresh tomatoes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine 1st 5 ingredients.
Add together beaten eggs, cooking oil, vanilla, and buttermilk.
Mix with dry ingredients and stir in blueberries.
Makes 18 muffins.
Cook at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes. Oven temperature may vary.

title: souper easy quiche
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add soup and cream, mixing well.
Sprinkle cheese, ham and broccoli evenly over pie crust.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: rich cocoa balls
directions: Combine powdered sugar and cocoa in large mixer bowl.
Add sweetened condensed milk and vanilla; blend well.
Stir in nuts. Cover bowl tightly; chill for about 30 minutes.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in powdered sugar to coat completely.
Place in storage container; cover tightly.
Chill for at least 2 hours, or until firm.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Mix sugar and the cinnamon and set aside.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles corn meal.
Add milk and stir until dough stiffens; turn out on floured board and knead until dough is well mixed.
Roll out into an oblong approximately 8 x 16-inches.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar/cinnamon mixture. Roll into long roll and cut into 16 (1-inch) sections.
Place into small muffin tins and bake at 450° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Put sugar, vinegar, water and salt in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Now, add just the beet juice and boil for 2 more minutes.
Put shelled eggs in container and pour boiled mixture over.
Add beets.
Ready to eat next day.
(When hard-boiling eggs, add salt to the water.
This makes the shells come off easier.)

title: carnival casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and green peppers.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, spices, syrup and salsa.
Cook macaroni and add cubed Velveeta.
Add ground beef mixture to this.
Bake at 375°, covered, for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak red beans overnight.
Simmer in same water until tender, 2 to 3 hours.
Drain and save water.
Place in layers:
beans, bacon and onions.
Combine ketchup, molasses, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Pour over beans.
Add enough water to cover pot and bake.
The last half of baking time, uncover pot.
Add a little water if beans seem dry while baking.
Bake at 325° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly.
Place in crock-pot.
Mix soups together with milk; pour over chicken.
Add onion and carrots; season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on low for approximately 6 hours.

title: peppermint marble cake
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Add extract.
Divide batter in half.
Tint half pink.
Spoon alternately into pan.
Top with candy.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Let cool and remove from pan.
Then munch out!

title: microwavable scrambled eggs
directions: Use as many eggs as needed for desired serving(s).
For 2 eggs, put in a small glass bowl for 45 seconds; stir with a fork on High; then 20 more seconds.
For 1 dozen eggs, set microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir with a fork, then return to microwave for additional 1 minute.
Could use less or more seconds, depending on desired style of scrambled eggs.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix
together in a 9 x 9-inch square pan, reserving 1/2 cup of cracker crumbs for topping.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: blackberry jam bars
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and beat well.
Add salt, baking soda and flour.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and press one half of mixture into baking pan.
Spread with jam and sprinkle rest of mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Boil sugar and milk until soft ball stage.
Add one package pitted dates, chopped fine.
Cook until dates are dissolved, stirring constantly.
Add nuts and pour on damp cloth.
Roll into log shape.
Chill.
Slice thin and serve.

title: ice cream pumpkin squares
directions: Mix crumbs and butter. Press into a buttered 8-inch square pan. Reserve some crumbs for the top. Combine the sugar and spices with the pumpkin. Fold in the ice cream. Pour into the crumb crust. Freeze. Cut into squares and top with reserved crumbs, whipped cream and nuts.

title: "quick and easy" mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Mix all soups and green chilies with meat; stir and simmer until hot. Grate cheese and cut your onion up (not too small).
You'll need a large, deep pan.
Put some chips in the pan (enough to cover bottom).
Put some mixture on top of the chips (use sparingly). Put onion and cheese over this; do not mix together.
(Be sure and save some onion and cheese.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream the sugar, oil and margarine.
Sift flour and dry ingredients.
Add eggs to creamed mixture alternately with flour mixture.
Mix well, then add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven.
Cool for 10 minutes and glaze.
Also good without glaze.

title: brown gravy
directions: Fry your meat.
Drain your grease, leaving about 2 tablespoons of grease in pan with your meat drippings.
Cut up a small onion and brown.
Then, put in flour and brown.
Add water to desired thickness.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook rice and drain, pouring cold water over rice and drain well.
Mix all together the other ingredients with rice; then add almonds.
Then put corn flakes in melted margarine; mix well.
Put in baking dish and then pour the corn flakes and butter on top. Bake at 350° 20 to 30 minutes or until flakes are golden brown.

title: zucchini cookies(your kids will love them!)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
You do not need to grease cookie sheets. Mix all ingredients together well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake from 6 to 10 minutes, depending on oven.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Press one pkg. of crescent rolls into bottom of greased 9 x 13 pan. Take up the sides a little.
Cream together cream cheese, vanilla and 1 c. sugar.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Add other pkg. of crescent rolls as next layer.
Melt oleo and pour over top.
Finally sprinkle with the 1/4 c. of sugar and 2 tsp. cinnamon mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.
325° for a glass pan.
Serve warm.

title: elegant eggs
directions: Mix together beaten eggs, milk and all other ingredients except bacon.
Refrigerate overnight in a covered dish.
When ready to bake, pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with fried and crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: frozen passion
directions: Pour Eagle Brand milk and pop into freezer.
Freeze according to ice cream maker directions.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: recipe for a happy marriage
directions: Take one large, grassy field, one half dozen children, assorted sizes, two or three small dogs, a pinch of brook and some pebbles.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and salt with electric mixer until eggs begin to turn light in color.
Slowly add sugar and continue beating for 10 to 15 minutes.
Blend in Milnot and vanilla, pour mixture into gallon freezer and fill with whole milk.

title: layered hamburg casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onions and drain. Put in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Drain string beans and layer on hamburg.
Dilute chicken soup with milk.
Pour over beans.
Cover with layer of potato Tater Tots.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: garlic shrimp
directions: Melt butter
in skillet with lid.
Add remaining ingredients, including shrimp in shells.
Toss well.
Set aside for 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Place over medium heat.
Stir and cover. Cook
for
minutes.
Shrimp
should
turn pink. Serve immediately over rice.
Serves 4.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Whirl in blender.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator to thicken.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken til done, debone and cut-up into bite size pieces.
Reserve broth.
Dip tortillas into broth.
Line tortillas into 9 x 13 pan.
Mix soups, chili powder, onions, chicken, and Ro-tel tomatoes and layer over tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese. Repeat layers ending with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix graham crackers, 1/3 cup sugar and butter; press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix eggs, 3/4 cup sugar and cream cheese; pour over crust. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cook pumpkin, egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, milk, salt and cinnamon until mixture thickens. Remove from heat and add gelatin, dissolved in cold water. Cool. Beat egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar; fold in pumpkin mixture. Pour over cooled baked crust. Top with whipped cream.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Drain fruit; mix juice, sugar, flour and egg yolks.
Cook until like pudding.
Refrigerate overnight. Add Cool Whip before serving.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Butter sides and bottom of 8 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread green chiles on sides and bottom of pan.
Alternate layers of zucchini, diced onion and cheese.
Beat 2 eggs lightly; add milk and Bisquick.
Mix well and pour over top of casserole.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until squash is tender in 325° oven.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour; add baking powder and salt.
Add shortening to dry ingredients.
Then add liquid.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut out with cutter that cuts round.
Put in greased pan.
Bake at 475° until done.

title: lizzy's grandma's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; cool and cube.
Chop onion.
Put first 5 ingredients in large bowl and blend.
Add remaining ingredients and toss until mixed.
Cover and chill 4 hours before serving.
This is one of Lizzy's favorite dishes!

title: shoo-fly cake bake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and oleo to crumbs.
Remove 1 cup of crumbs for topping.

title: fig-berry jam
directions: Wash figs and dry well.
Put through food chopper, using coarse blade, then measure.
Mix figs, sugar and gelatin together in saucepan.
Cook until thick, about 45 minutes, stirring often. Pour into jars and seal.
Makes 2 pints.

title: peach french toast
directions: In a saucepan, bring brown sugar, butter and water to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; top with peaches. Arrange bread over peaches. In a bowl, whisk the eggs, milk and vanilla; slowly pour over bread. Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight. Remove from the refrigerator 30 minutes before baking. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Uncover, bake 25 to 30 minutes longer or until the bread is golden brown. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken until tender using additional celery, onion and salt in water for seasoning.
Remove chicken from bones and skin; add celery, onion, eggs and pickles.
Moisten with chicken broth to cut down on Miracle Whip.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: hearty beef 'n cheese crescent pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large frypan, brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, beans, cumin seed, garlic salt and salt; simmer while preparing crust. Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place triangles in ungreased 9-inch pie pan; press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Combine egg and 1 cup cheese; spread over crust.
Spoon hot meat mixture into crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
For easier serving, let stand 5 minutes before cutting into wedges.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Stir in the extract and vanilla into the creamed mixture.
Alternately stir in the dry ingredients and the buttermilk.
Knead dough until smooth.
Roll out dough to 1/8 inch thickness on floured surface.
Cut into shapes.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into ungreased casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grape pie
directions: Heat grape juice and add cornstarch, sugar, butter, cinnamon and vanilla and cook until clear.
Add egg yolks which have been beaten, gradually, and cook 5 minutes.
Cool and pour into pie shell.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar; spread over pie and brown lightly.

title: mexican cranberry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan. Cook over low heat. Serve hot or chill for later.

title: dressed-up burgers
directions: Form beef into 8 thin patties.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Lay cheese slices on 4 patties.
Top with remaining 4 patties and pinch edges together.
Put in hot skillet.
Brown patties on one side, turn and while this side is browning, add tomato sauce. Simmer 8 to 10 minutes, basting occasionally.
Serve piping hot.

title: boeuf bourguignonne
directions: Cut tenderloin into 1-inch cubes.
Season with seasoning salt. Melt 2/3 of butter in a pan.
Braise beef cubes for 20 minutes. Saute mushrooms and shallots in the remaining 1/3 butter.
Stir flour into the vegetables.
Combine wine with all ingredients in pan.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 12 people.

title: 3 cheese chicken
directions: Season chicken to taste.
Take rice and put in casserole dish. Add water and bouillon cubes.
Place chicken on top.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute garlic in margarine, white wine and lemon juice in large skillet until soft.
Add enough shrimp to cover skillet bottom. (May have to saute in 2 batches.)
Cook until bottoms turn pink, approximately 3 minutes.
Turn to other side and cook another 3 minutes.
Transfer to serving dish and garnish with parsley. Serve over rice or pasta.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Cut rhubarb into 1/2-inch lengths.
Mix 2 tablespoons with 1 cup of sugar and mix with rhubarb.
Combine 1 cup of flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in egg.
Sprinkle over rhubarb.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cake cool.
Next punch holes in the top all over. Pour eagle brand milk over cake and let settle.
Pour cream of coconut over cake and let soak into cake.
Spread cool whip on top and sprinkle with coconut. refrigerate overnight or about 12 hours for better flavor.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to cooled, scalded milk. Combine the dry ingredients and add liquid; work into dough.
Be sure to add the last 1/4 cup of liquid slow enough to form firm ball.
Roll dough out 1/4 inch thick and cut into squares.
Fry only a few at a time.
Spoon over them to help them puff up.
May spread with butter and honey on top while still hot.

title: clever judy frosting
directions: Combine all in order given.
Place over cracked ice and beat 5 minutes or until right to spread.
Ices 1 large layer cake.

title: belgian tomatoes
directions: Arrange tomato slices on serving plate and top with onion rings.
Sprinkle with sugar, salt, pepper, celery seed, basil, dill weed and chives.
Pour dressing over all.
Chill.

title: praline coffee cake
directions: Grease tube pan.
Place frozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle pudding mix over rolls.
Melt butter and mix in remaining ingredients. Pour over rolls.
Cover.
Let stand overnight on counter.
Next morning, preheat oven to 350°.
Bake approximately 30 minutes. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes. Cut around pan edge.
Invert on plate and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place half the potatoes in bottom of greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with hamburger.
Add remaining potatoes.
Combine soup, milk, onion and green pepper.
Mix well.
Pour over potatoes. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: fresh corn salad
directions: Cut off corn kernels; set aside.
Combine water and sugar in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add corn and return to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Drain on paper towels, patting dry.
Combine corn, onion and remaining ingredients; let stand 30 minutes or cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Yields 12 servings.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Combine milk, egg whites, honey/molasses and oil.
Add to dry ingredients mixing just until moistened.
Spray bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups with vegetable cooking spray and fill cups evenly.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: baked beans
directions: Parboil beans until skins are tight.
Add remaining ingredients, then bake 11 hours at 250°.

title: dirt dessert
directions: First cream together the powdered sugar, butter and cream cheese in a bowl. Next, in another bowl, mix the instant pudding and milk together. After this is done, fold or mix them together. Now crush the Oreos in the blender.
Last put a layer of Oreos on the bottom of the serving dish, followed by a layer of pudding. Repeat until container is full.
Be sure Oreos are the top layer.

title: baked fruit
directions: Save some of the juice from the fruit.
Melt the stick of butter in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Pour a little pineapple juice over butter and the sugar.
Mix.
Add all the fruit. Put crushed crackers over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until syrupy. Cherries are optional.

title: shrimp soup
directions: Saute celery and onions for 3 minutes. Add hash browns for approximately 2 minutes. Combine balance of ingredients and heat, then simmer approximately 20 minutes.

title: zucchini beef skillet
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Add vegetables and spices. Cook together until vegetables are tender.
Add cheese until well blended.

title: busy lady (or gent) cobbler
directions: Use some of the margarine to grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the rest of the margarine and set aside.
Pour fruit and juice into buttered dish (sprinkle cinnamon on fruit if desired). Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit (sprinkle cinnamon over cake mix if desired).
Drizzle the melted margarine over dry cake mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chili relleno bake
directions: In a skillet, cook meat for a few minutes.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until done; drain.
Line a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with half the green chilies.
Top with 1 1/2 cups cheese. Add meat mixture on top with other half of chilies.
Set aside. Beat eggs and flour until smooth.
Add milk, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Blend well.
Pour over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and let melt.

title: refrigerator fruit cake
directions: Mix nuts, raisins and crackers.
Melt marshmallows in milk. Pour over other ingredients.
Pack in greased tube pan and let set in refrigerator until firm.

title: sloppy biscuits
directions: Spray pan with cooking spray.
Put biscuits in pan.
Cover biscuits with sugar, cinnamon and milk.
Don't quite cover biscuits with milk.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes.
Remove and eat.

title: light 'n easy biscuits
directions: In a bowl combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Add milk and stir until blended.
Place dough on lightly floured surface. Knead lightly.
Roll dough to a 9-inch square. Place dough into ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Cut through dough in squares. Bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes.
When baked, biscuits will separate at cut lines.

title: honey apple cake
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and honey.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to honey mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla, nuts and apples.
Mix gently and pour into a lightly greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Brown beef; add chili sauce.
Mix and heat.
Use 1 jar chili sauce for each 1 pound of hamburger.

title: oriental pepper steak
directions: Cover steak strips with Fresca.
Simmer meat until almost tender.
Add vegetables, soy sauce and vinegar.
Heat through.

title: minted nuts
directions: Slowly cook sugar, water, corn syrup and salt.
Remove from heat just before syrup reaches soft ball stage.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Add peppermint and nuts; stir with a circular motion until every nut is coated and mixture begins to look creamy.
Empty on waxed paper; cool, then separate.
May be stored in cans for weeks!

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten chicken breasts with mallet. Take 1 slice of cheese and 1 slice of ham and roll up in chicken breast.
Roll chicken in cracker crumbs and seasonings.
Place in glass baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: taco soup
directions: Makes a full crock-pot. Brown hamburger and drain. Mix all together and cook all day. Serve with shredded Cheddar cheese, sour cream and corn chips or Doritos Scoops.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine milk, potatoes, shortening, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl; let stand until lukewarm.
Add yeast, softened in water and eggs.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and beat well.
Cover and set in warm place 1 hour or until full of bubbles.
Stir in 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 cups flour to make a fairly stiff dough.
Knead until smooth on lightly floured surface.
Return to greased mixing bowl; grease top of dough.
Cover and chill in refrigerator.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon (diced) until crisp and leave enough grease in skillet to mix flour, vinegar, sugar, mustard and water.
Cook until thick and add sliced, cooked potatoes, onion and green pepper.
Stir.
Serve warm or cold.
Decorate with sliced, hard-boiled eggs.

title: vickie's slow-cooker vegetable soup
directions: In large skillet, saute onion, celery and pepper until crisp-tender.
Add potato and garlic; saute an additional 3-5 minutes.
Transfer to 5-quart crockpot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low for 9-10 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Discard bay leaf before serving.

title: red pepper relish
directions: Cut peppers and onions in half lengthwise, slice thinly.
Or grind peppers and onions, reserving juices.
In saucepan, combine juices, peppers, onions, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour into hot, clean jars.
Seal.
Makes 10 half-pints.

title: saucy ham and potato bake
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly until thick.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese. Stir until melted.
Toss potatoes in cheese sauce.
Pour in casserole dish, reserving 1 cup potato slices. Arrange ham and remaining potato slices on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: caviness special pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add your flavor.
Put in your flour, one cup at a time.
Add your milk.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Wash fruit and measure into a shallow baking dish.
Combine the tapioca, sugar, salt and spices.
Stir in blackberries and let stand for 10 minutes.
Dot top with butter.
Roll biscuit dough to thickness of 1/4-inch.
Prick and arrange over top of fruit mixture.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 minutes or until well browned.
Serves 6
to 8.

title: cheese omelet
directions: Beat eggs, cream, seasonings and baking powder until well blended.
Place butter in glass pie plate.
Cook on Roast (7) for 1 minute or until melted.
Pour egg mixture into hot butter.
Cook on Medium (5) for 6 to 8 minutes or until center is almost set. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Fold in half and serve.
Serves 2.

title: pea cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Coat eggplant slices with flour and dip into beaten eggs. Brown in vegetable oil on both sides.
Remove from heat.
Mix together Ricotta, 1 egg, salt, pepper and Romano cheese.
Place slice of Mozzarella cheese and a spoonful of Ricotta mixture into eggplant slice and roll up.
Place seam side dough in a baking pan. Repeat.
Cover with marinara sauce.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Romano cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mother's pot pie
directions: Roll thin and cut into squares.
Drop into boiling broth and cook 15 to 20 minutes, covered.

title: chicken salad polynesian
directions: Thin mayonnaise with lemon or lime juice.
Mix thoroughly with first 3 ingredients.
Add pineapple and nuts and toss.
Serve with guava or banana bread.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg and combine with vinegar and water.
Sprinkle over flour and mix. Wrap in wax paper and chill 30 minutes.
Can be kept in refrigerator up to 1 week or divide into 4 parts.
Wrap each and freeze.
Makes 4 shells or 2 double pies.

title: shrimp and cream cheese appetizer
directions: Place the cream cheese on desired dish.
Pour shrimp cocktail over cream cheese.
Serve with crackers, i.e., Triscuits.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots; drain.
Cook onion in saucepan with oleo for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard, then milk, stirring until smooth.
Add pepper and celery salt.
In 2-quart casserole dish layer carrots and cheese.
Pour on sauce.
Top with bread crumbs.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt cream cheese.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.
Makes 2 3/4 cups.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Mix with white or brown sugar, cornstarch and lemon juice.
Turn into baked pie shell.

title: quick chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions and drain. Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine until they are lightly browned.
Combine the spaghetti, onion mixture, soup, chicken, pimentos and 1 cup of the cheese.
Pour into a large casserole and sprinkle with the other cup of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: italian delight
directions: Cook meat in fat 10 minutes.
Add onions, pepper and garlic. Cook 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Add soups and corn.
Let simmer for 30 minutes, then add cooked noodles and sliced cheese.
Simmer until cheese melts.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not beat.
Bake in 3 greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Check for doneness.
Cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add melted margarine to dressing.
Add half to mixture.
Pat in greased casserole.
Cover with remaining dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Mix eggs and milk.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put some cheese and bread crumbs on top. Bake until done.

title: okra and corn medley
directions: In large nonstick skillet, heat oil.
Cook onion and garlic until onion is translucent, about 5 minutes.
Add tomato, okra, broth and thyme.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Stir in corn, chili pepper, salt (if desired) and black pepper.
Cook about 5 additional minutes or until of desired tenderness.
Yields 4 servings.
Contains 133 calories, 3 grams fat.

title: bleu cheese flank steak
directions: Have butcher cut a pocket in steak.
Saute mushrooms in one tablespoon	butter.
Add remaining butter, cheese, garlic, salt and pepper;
cool.	Stuff
into
pocket
and
close
with skewers. Broil 3 inches from flame to desired doneness.

title: best oatmeal cookies(yield: 55 servings)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg whites.
In a medium size bowl, combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to sugar mixture. Stir in oats, raisins and vanilla.
Chill 1 hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: Preheat oil in skillet, uncovered, at 325°.
Add meat and brown.
Add onion and pepper slices and cook until just tender. Dissolve cornstarch in soy sauce and water.
Add brown sugar and pepper.
Pour into skillet, stirring, until sauce is thickened and clear.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: asparagus chicken rice casserole
directions: Spread rice in a 7 x 11-inch cake pan.
Add chicken broth and mushrooms.
Dot with butter.
Place breasts in center.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Spoon mushroom soup over.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Arrange asparagus around outer edges of pan. Brush with melted butter; sprinkle with paprika. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes longer or until asparagus is tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: split pea soup(low-fat)
directions: Rinse peas in running cold water and discard any stones or shriveled peas.
Set aside.
In a 6-quart Dutch oven over medium heat, cook celery and onion in chicken broth or small amount of water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce to low.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until peas are very tender, stirring occasionally.
Discard bay leaf.
Fill blender 3/4 full at a time.
Cover and puree.
Pour into bowl and repeat.
Return to pot and keep hot.
Serve with a spoonful of nonfat plain yogurt. Very low-fat, virtually none.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries. Add drained pineapple, banana and marshmallows.
Pour 1/2 in jello mold or salad bowl.
Allow time to set in refrigerator.
Top with sour cream.
Pour remaining salad mixture on top.
Refrigerate several hours.
Unmold on pretty plate or serve from bowl.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: In ice cream freezer can, place first five ingredients.
Slice bananas into the can.
Add next four ingredients up to the fill line.
Stir well.
Freeze and enjoy.
Makes 1 gallon ice cream.

title: chicken and artichoke salad
directions: Mix ingredients and serve in salad bowl.
Better if made a day before.
An easy and elegant salad.

title: little indian dish
directions: Saute beef, onion and green pepper until meat is done.
Add mushroom soup and stewed tomatoes and cook on low heat until onion and green pepper is done.
Add cooked long grain rice and blend well.
Pour into casserole dish, then garnish top with grated cheese.
Place in a 400° oven until cheese melts.
Also good warmed over.
Add the catsup and chili powder when adding the soup and stewed tomatoes.

title: love cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add margarine and soda dissolved in water.
Let cool, then add 2 cups flour and 1 teaspoon baking powder.
Spread on a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
While warm, ice with 1 tablespoon butter melted in very little milk.
Add confectioners sugar until thick.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: ma's pickles
directions: Peel and core cucumbers then slice and cover with cold water for 4 hours.
Drain. Mix all ingredients except cucumbers.
Add cucumbers; bring to boil then simmer for 20 minutes.
Pack in jars 1/2 inch below top of jar.
Seal at once.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Pour over crackers.
Stir to coat.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes.
Stir gently.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes more.
Store in an airtight container.

title: stack cake
directions: Dress a pair of half grown chickens, split down one side of backbone, cut breastbone so fowl will lay flat in roast pan.

Let remain on ice overnight, then place in roaster, breasts downward. Add a lump of butter and three teacups of boiling water, salt and let gently simmer on top of stove three hours, adding very small quantities of water as needed.
Let fowl fry down in liquor; place on flat hot dish with spatula, breast upward.
Pour a rich cream gravy around fowl and garnish with parsley.
Flour that has been previously browned should be used in making gravy.

title: lisa's pork chop casserole
directions: Salt and pepper chops to taste.
Put rice in bottom of baking dish.
Mix soups and water.
Pour over rice.
Melt butter. Dip chops in butter, then roll in Ritz crackers.
Lay on top of rice mixture. Cover with foil. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a large frypan, saute onion in margarine.
Blend in flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add broth and cook until thick and bubbly. Stir continuously.
Add remaining ingredients and continue to heat.
Pour into pastry lined 9-inch pan.
Cover with top crust. Make slits in top crust to allow steam to vent while baking.
May need to put foil on edges to prevent overbaking.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast.
Mix (I use low speed of mixer).

title: hermits
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar together. Add milk and molasses. Add sifted dry ingredients, then raisins. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Nuts may be added or substituted for raisins.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cover with crushed potato chips and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Brown in vegetable oil and drain.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In an ungreased 1 1/2-quart baking dish, mix pie filling and almond extract.
Place in oven for 15 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: pumpkin cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Paper line or grease 24 muffin cups. Blend cake mix, pumpkin, eggs, vegetable oil and water in large mixer bowl until moistened. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour batter into prepared muffin cups, filling 3/4 full. Bake for 18 to 23 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Spread cupcakes with frosting. Decorate with assorted sprinkles, if desired.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to soft ball stage, then add other three ingredients and pour into buttered dish.
Cools real fast.

title: country fried steak
directions: Sprinkle 13 x 9-inch baking pan with flour.
Put beef in pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle top of meat with flour. Bake in oven at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: no bake brownies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a full boil, for five to six minutes.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in remaining ingredients.
Press into 9-inch buttered pan.
Chill one hour.

title: dried beef cream cheese ball
directions: Mix and form ball.
Cover with slices of dried beef.

title: fresh homemade (texan) salsa
directions: Place tomatoes in blender; blend until they are a chunky consistency.
Add chopped onion and chopped green peppers.
Blend 20 to 30 seconds.
Heat pricked lime in microwave for 10 to 20 seconds.
Cut lime and squeeze juice into salsa mixture.
Discard lime.
Add minced garlic, chopped cilantro, tomato paste and chopped jalapeno peppers to mixture.
Stir and refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.
Yields 6 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: brewed tea
directions: Brew tea.
When done, pour tea syrup into 1 gallon jug.
Add sugar.
Dissolve, and fill gallon jug to top with cold water.

title: a-2-fay
directions: Melt butter in skillet, then saute onions, green peppers and celery in the butter for about 20 minutes.
Add soups and seasonings, stirring until smooth, then add shrimp.
Cook on medium heat for about 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: bite-size cheese balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in pecans.
Cover and chill.
To serve, place a pretzel in each ball.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; rinse with cold water.
In large bowl, mix first 7 ingredients.
Toss with Italian dressing. Cover and chill several hours. At serving time, toss with tomato and avocado.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: last minute corn salad
directions: Combine corn and salad dressing.
Stir in corn chips just before serving.

title: hot dip
directions: Mix all together.
Then add 1/2 cup sour cream.
Heat in microwave.

title: pizza buns
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Split buns and lightly butter each half. Sprinkle with garlic salt. Brown hamburger, well. Drain. Set aside. Spread pizza sauce over each bun half. Sprinkle lightly with oregano. Add hamburger to each bun and top with cheeses. Bake in oven until cheeses are melted. You may add any other ingredients you like on pizza.

title: fruit cobbler cake
directions: Sift together the salt, flour, cinnamon, cloves and baking powder.
Cream the remaining ingredients, except candied fruit and/or raisins.
Add the creamed mixture alternately to the sifted mixture.
Add the candied fruit and raisins.
Bake in loaf pan at 350°.

title: salmon marinade
directions: Will marinate up to 2 pounds salmon.
Marinate two or more hours before grilling.
Grill on Reynolds Wrap on medium heat 20 minutes on one side.
Brush on marinade while cooking.
Turn over and grill other side 20 minutes or until "flaky."
Serve immediately.

title: fish baked in milk
directions: Place the fish in bottom of glass pan.
Cover with milk up to top of fish.
Dot in several places with butter.
Seasonings may be added.
Bake at 325° until flaky, about 75 minutes.

title: hot chinese-style cabbage slaw
directions: Pack cabbage in 2-quart jar or container with tight-fitting lid.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover tight; let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Will keep refrigerated up to two weeks. Makes 10 servings.

title: sausage-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms. Chop stems. Set mushrooms and stems aside.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook sausage until well browned.
With slotted spoon, remove sausage to paper towels to drain. Spoon off all but 2 tablespoons drippings from skillet.
In hot drippings over medium heat, cook mushroom stems until tender, about 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove skillet from heat.
Stir in sausage, cheese and crumbs.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Fill mushroom caps with sausage mixture.
Place stuffed mushrooms in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly-roll pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan; line pan with waxed paper and grease again.
In mixing bowl, combine chocolate morsels, crushed graham crackers and sweetened condensed milk.
Press mixture into prepared pan.

title: bran rolls(mrs. jack l. pritchard)
directions: Pour boiling water over All-Bran, sugar, shortening and salt. Let sugar and shortening melt; cool.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Pour into first mixture.
Add eggs and flour; mix well. Cover bowl and let dough rise until doubled in bulk.
Knead dough; roll to 1 1/2-inches thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Put in greased pan, let rise and bake at 425°.

title: jean's no. 1 pork chops
directions: Bake chops standing up for 2 hours at 350°.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Heat sauce first and pour over chops.
Bake 45 minutes more.
Baste with sauce as needed.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut and cube potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes after peeling.
Boil until done, but not breaking apart.
Peel and cube eggs in 1/2-inch cubes.
Cut onion in 1/4-inch cubes.
Add all ingredients to potatoes.
Add mayonnaise and stir until well mixed, adding more mayonnaise if needed for desired consistency.

title: speedy supper bread
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Stir in salt, sugar and pepper. When browned, add tomato sauce.
Simmer while preparing bread.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Chill 3 hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: gwen's marinated tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes in wedges. Mix remaining ingredients in bowl, pour over tomatoes and let marinate 24 hours.

title: keebler peach crunch
directions: Arrange peaches in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until topping is golden brown.
Serve with desired cream or Cool Whip.

title: bourbon wieners
directions: Cook onion in butter.
Add catsup, brown sugar and bourbon. Cut wieners on the bias into bite-size pieces.
Add to sauce. Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour or until sauce begins to glaze, stirring occasionally.
If sauce gets too thick, add more bourbon.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg.
Beat.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour milk.
Add vanilla or lemon flavoring.
Roll out and cut.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry and pecan cake
directions: Beat eggs in mixer bowl until foamy.
Add oil, gelatin, strawberries and milk; beat well.
Add cake mix; beat well.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until layers test done.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Spread frosting between layers and over top and side of cake.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: favorite caramel frosting
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar in a heavy saucepan; place over medium heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar melts and syrup is light golden brown.
Combine remaining 2 1/2 cups sugar, milk, beaten egg and salt, stirring well; stir in butter.
Stir butter mixture into hot caramelized sugar.
(The mixture will tend to lump, becoming smooth with further cooking.)
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until a candy thermometer registers 230° (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Cool 5 minutes.
Beat with a wooden spoon to almost spreading consistency (about 5 minutes) and spread on cooled cake.
Yield:
about 2 1/2 cups.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Place in baking dish. Cover with cracker crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat until blended.
Makes almost 1 quart.
Serve in hollowed out round loaf of bread.
Dip bread chunks in dip.
Can add 1 small can of shrimp.

title: corn meal waffles
directions: Mix well with a wire whisk.
Fry in a lightly oiled waffle iron.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, onions and peppers.
(Strain; be sure to get all water out.)
Add other ingredients (tie spices in cloth and put in mixture).
Boil for 40 minutes.
Stir well while cooking.
Seal while hot.

title: fluffy pineapple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt;
add pineapple juice.
Blend well. Cook
over low heat until thick.
Add a small amount of hot mixture
to
well
beaten
eggs.
Stir
into remaining hot mixture,
cook
until
thick.
Add	marshmallows.
Stir
well, until melted.
Add	well
drained
pineapple and chill 1 hour. Fold in 1/2 of whipped cream and pour into baked pastry shell. Top with
remaining whip cream.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Best if longer.

title: raspberry salad
directions: May add crushed nuts.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix cucumbers, peppers and onions together.
Salt to taste. Let stand overnight.
Drain.
Add clear water and drain again.

title: mom's cranberry sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and refrigerate overnight.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Select tender squash, light yellow in color and free from blemishes. Do not peel; slice in wheels. Prepare green chiles; chop chiles and season with garlic salt. Grate cheese. Using an 8-inch baking dish, line with a layer of squash, then layer cheese, cracker crumbs and repeat ending with a layer of cheese. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain cooked broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onion, salt and pepper.
Add to broccoli and pour into 8 x 4-inch dish. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing mix and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: striped jello
directions: Prepare 1 box Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish and refrigerate.
Scald milk and sugar. Soften gelatin in cold water; add to milk and sugar.
Let cool to lukewarm, then stir or beat in sour cream until smooth.
When first Jell-O is set, pour on 1 cup of filling; refrigerate until set.
Make second box of Jell-O so it will be at room temperature by the time the white layer is set.
Keep alternating layers, ending with Jell-O.
If the kitchen is cool, the white stuff will keep trying to set up in the pan.
Just heat a little and stir until liquified and smooth.
You can use just red and green Jell-O for Christmas.

title: crab ball appetizer
directions: Form cream cheese into ball; form crab meat over the ball. Top with cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: eclair cake
directions: Open frosting and set in a pan of hot water.
Beat pudding and milk together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer graham crackers and pudding, ending with graham crackers.
Stir frosting and pour over graham crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, except cream cheese.
Mix in cream cheese.
Form ball.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage lasagna wraps
directions: Cook and drain lasagna noodles.
Divide smoked sausage into 6 pieces.
Split lengthwise and stuff with 1/2 slice Mozzarella cheese.
Wrap each piece in a noodle.
Place in baking dish and cover with Italian cooking sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: crabmeat canapes
directions: Soften butter and cheese to room temperature.
Blend cheese, butter and salts.
Add crabmeat to mixture.
Cut muffins in half. Spread mixture on muffins.
Freeze until ready to use.
When ready, thaw for 10 minutes.
Slice into eighths.
Place on cookie sheets and broil for 2 minutes or until bubbly.
Or bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Yields 96.

title: mama's ho-bo stew
directions: Brown beef in skillet, if lot of fat drain.
Add onions, brown beef and onions.
Pour into large stew pot.
Add tomatoes; bring to boil.
Add stew mix, simmer until veggies are done.

title: stuffed yellow squash with bacon
directions: Boil squash in plenty of salt water about 15 minutes or until just tender; do not overcook.
Take squash out of water, being careful not to break the neck of the squash.
Cut squash in half lengthwise on through the neck.
With a teaspoon, scoop out pulp (seeds, if tender, are edible) for the filling.
Set aside.
Place squash shells on a shallow greased baking dish.
In a small pan, cook onion with bacon drippings until tender.
Add squash pulp. Cook until most of the moisture is cooked out.
Spoon mixture into the 6 shells.
Sprinkle Ritz crumbs over all, then the crumbled bacon.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, sweet milk, salt, eggs, soda and corn in one bowl.
Also mix bacon drippings, onion, pepper, ground beef and Cheddar cheese.
Grease a heavy skillet and heat.
Sprinkle with meal and pour in half of batter and beef mixture.
Pour on remaining batter and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: skillet zucchini and sausage
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet; lightly brown sausage.
Add onion, celery, green pepper, garlic, oregano and pepper.
Cook and stir until vegetables are almost tender.
Add zucchini and tomatoes; cook and stir until zucchini is just tender.
Sprinkle with seasoning blend.
Yield: 8 to 10 side dish servings.

title: mom's carrot cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and bring to boil.
Turn down to simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool to room temperature.
This is a must.
In a large bowl mix the dry ingredients.
Now fold liquid mixture into dry ingredients.
Mix with spoon until well mixed.
Add applesauce and nuts.
Put mixture in Bundt pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours (or until toothpick is clean).

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes in upper half of oven at 400°.

title: amish ground beef grand style
directions: Mix everything together except cheese and Tater Tots.
Put in pan.
Put a layer of cheese over the hamburger then Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for several hours and roll in fresh parsley.

title: hazel's cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, milk and nuts.
Press half of this mixture in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels in top of double boiler with evaporated milk.
Sprinkle chocolate bits over baked layer; pour melted caramel over and swirl into chocolate.
Pat remaining cake mixture over caramel and chocolate layer.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes longer; cool.
Cut into squares.
Yields 48.

title: quick caramel icing
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add milk, stir until it boils.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Add sugar and beat until it has spreading consistency.

title: nachos
directions: Put tinfoil on a cookie sheet.
Spread chips to cover the whole sheet.
Spread cheeses across the top.
Spread hamburg with diced onions and green peppers across the top.
Add more cheese, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and picante sauce.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Cube potatoes and place in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cover with sliced cheese, sprinkle chopped onion over cheese.
Mix butter and bread cubes together and place over onion.
Sprinkle with parsley, paprika, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable stuffed manicotti
directions: Soak No Boil lasagna noodles in warm water for 5 minutes or until softened, taking care they do not stick together.
Combine next 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Set aside.

title: potato salad with string beans
directions: Boil potatoes with skin; peel and slice.
Boil separately 1 pound string beans.
Let potatoes and string beans cool.
Add to mixture the chopped scallions, fresh parsley, fresh dill, salad oil and vinegar; mix gently and serve.

title: green rice
directions: Saute margarine, celery and onions.
Mix with soup, cheese and broccoli.
Add rice.
Pour into long, greased casserole dish. Cook 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pumpkin nut roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes, then beat in sugar gradually.
Stir in lemon juice and pumpkin.
In separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and pumpkin pie spice.
Mix this into pumpkin mixture.
Grease and flour a 15-inch cookie sheet, then pour mixture in.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over all.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Punch has a perky tart flavor.

title: chicken and okra gumbo
directions: Boil chicken in water in large pot, about 30 to 45 minutes. Remove chicken and reserve broth.
Bone and cube chicken; set aside.
In large pot, combine oil and flour until smooth.
Cook over medium-high heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to medium.
