Cook and stir about 5 minutes more or until mixture is reddish-brown.
Turn the heat to high.
Stir in 4 cups of reserved broth, mixing well.
Cook and stir until thickened. Add onions, celery, green pepper and garlic; cook and stir for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, okra, bay leaves, basil, salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add additional seasonings to taste.
Stir in chicken; heat through.
Serve with rice.
Great meat!

title: margaret's tropical punch
directions: Thaw juices and combine in large container.
Add water and sugar.
Stir well and chill.
Add ginger ale.
Pour punch into bowl with block of ice.
With a toothpick, fit cherries into pineapple slices.
Float in punch bowl with banana and lime slices.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until brown, stir to crumble.
Drain, spoon beef into 8-inch baking dish.
Top with Pizza Quick, then cheese. Combine biscuit mix, milk and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over casserole covering evenly.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Layer fresh strawberries in baked pie crust. In a saucepan, bring vanilla pudding and water to boil. Remove from heat and stir in strawberry jello. Pour mixture over strawberries in crust. Cool. Serve with fat-free or light Cool Whip.

title: double chocolate snack cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour square pan.
In bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Pour into pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Blend together with remaining ingredients.
Bake in 3 small loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: italian sausage sandwiches
directions: In pan, cook sausage until no pink remains.
Drain fat.
Stir in pizza sauce and mushrooms.
Heat through.
Hollow out bottom halves of rolls.
Spoon in meat mixture.
Top with pepper rings and cheese.
Cover with bun tops.
Place sandwiches in a baking pan or sheet.
Cover tightly with foil and heat in a 375° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage joes
directions: Crumble sausage into medium skillet.
Add onion and pepper. Cook over medium heat until sausage is browned.
Drain off any drippings.
Stir in all remaining ingredients, except buns.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve hot on toasted buns.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute vegetables.
Saute ground beef. Mix together vegetables, beef and tomato paste.
Spread mixture in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top of beef mixture.
Unroll package of crescent rolls and place on top of cheese to cover.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 15 minutes, until pastry is golden brown.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread mix.
Cool and crumble; set aside.
Mix tomatoes, onion, green pepper and bacon with mayonnaise, pickle relish, pickle juice and milk if needed for good consistency. Place half of cornbread crumbs in casserole dish.
Cover with 1/2 of filling.
Place rest of crumbs next.
End with rest of dressing.
Let set at least 2 hours.

title: fanny farmer fudge
directions: Cut up marshmallows in a bowl.
Cook sugar and Carnation milk for 5 minutes at full rolling boil.
Stir constantly.
Pour over cut up ingredients (nuts, bars, marshmallows, chips, vanilla and salt).
Beat vigorously until marshmallows dissolve.
Grease pan. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: firehouse chili
directions: In a large saucepan saute beef, onion, green pepper, salt, black pepper and cayenne in 1 tbsp. butter until browned.
Add tomatoes and kidney beans and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Great served with warm breadsticks or garlic bread.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: In a glass of warm water, put 2 heaping teaspoons of cocoa mix.
Can substitute warm milk in place of water.

title: belle foust's carrot pickles
directions: Soak carrots, onions, cauliflower, cucumbers and peppers individually in weak salt water overnight.
Cook individually in same water, just until tender.
Pour off water.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube or 12-cup Bundt pan.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over bottom of pan.
Stir dry pudding mix into the cake mix.
Mix the cake ingredients together as per package directions.
Pour cake batter over the nuts.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 25 minutes; then invert on serving plate to finish cooling.
Prick top of cake.
Drizzle glaze over top and sides allowing cake to absorb it.
Repeat until glaze is used.

title: zucchini bake
directions: In 2-quart shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch), combine all ingredients except stuffing mix and butter.
Toss stuffing mix with butter and spoon over vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Makes 6 cups.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in large punch bowl.
Raspberries float to the top and if added when partially frozen will help keep punch chilled.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well, except cornflakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Pour in buttered casserole.
Top with crushed cornflakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Do not cover. This can be mixed and frozen for use later.

title: delicious oyster stew
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Add cheese just before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spiced banana coffee ring
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9-cup Bundt pan.
Pour 1/4 cup of melted butter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup of brown sugar and 1/3 cup of nuts evenly over butter.
Mix together mashed bananas, egg and sugar.
Stir in baking mix and milk.
Mix together brown sugar, nuts, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Spoon half of banana mixture into prepared pan.
Top with brown sugar-spice mixture. Drizzle with remaining melted butter.
Spoon over remaining banana mixture.
Smooth top.
Bake cake until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean, about 25 minutes.
Immediately invert pan onto a serving plate for 3 to 4 minutes, allowing syrup to drizzle over cake.
Remove pan.
Cool.

title: sailboats
directions: You will need paper and wooden picks for sails.

title: guam red rice
directions: Soak achote seeds in 1/2 cup of warm water for 30 minutes. Add salt.
Rub or press achote seeds to get color.
Strain liquid into small bowl.
Saute onions in oil.
Add rinsed rice to boiling achote-colored water.
Reduce heat to medium-high for 5 minutes or until water evaporates.
Reduce heat to low for 15 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: vegetable manicotti
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package; drain.
Arrange in single layer to fill.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: semolina cake - "torcik grysikowy" in polish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate the eggs.
Cream together the yolks and sugar.
Add salt, semolina and vanilla.
Beat egg whites stiff and dry.
Fold them into the yolk mixture.
Spread the batter into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until dry. Heat the milk to boiling.
When cake is done, gradually pour the boiling milk over it until it is all absorbed.
Warm warm or cold with custard sauce or whipped cream.

title: "chess bars"
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 13 pan. (I use my food processor.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, onion, carrot, 1/2 stick margarine, sour cream, soup and 1/2 package dressing mix.
Pour into oblong baking dish. Mix 1/2 stick margarine and remainder (1/2 package) dressing mix together; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350°, covered, for approximately 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook beef and garlic until beef is browned.
Add broccoli and onion. Cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over noodles. Makes 4 servings.

title: beef casserole
directions: Layer or place all ingredients in a casserole.
Bake, covered, three hours at 350°.
During the last 15 minutes, you may add peas.
The last few minutes, thicken with flour and water.
Serves at least 6.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Put all ingredients
into mixing bowl.
Beat for 3 minutes. Bake in long pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Pour hot icing over cake while it is still hot.

title: microwave baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter.
Put into greased baking dish.
Add dabs of butter over top.
Bake 10 minutes on high in microwave oven.
Stir after 5 minutes.
Test with knife.

title: mexican chicken pasta salad
directions: Prepare salad as directed on package except omit oil from dressing and mix in sour cream and red pepper.
Stir in chicken. Line serving plate with tortilla chips.
Mound salad onto chips; top with tomato and cheese.
Garnish with guacamole and sliced ripe olives, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Mix in barbecue sauce, onion, and brown sugar.

title: corny chicken
directions: Bake in casserole dish with crackers on top. Cook at 350 until bubbly or firm.

title: spinach casserole or spinach souffle
directions: Let spinach thaw and drain.
Squeeze out all liquid. Thoroughly mix flour, cottage cheese, spinach and melted butter. Add diced cheese, then slightly beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon pull apart bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13x9 pan, coat bottom of pan with 2 tbsp. margarine and 1 tsp. cinnamon.
Let the dough rise and thaw according to the package instructions.
When dough is ready, break off medium size pieces, roll into a ball and place in buttered pan.
In a saucepan, combine both puddings, brown sugar, margarine and cinnamon.
Cook on low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat when mixture begins to boil.
Pour over dough. Bake 20-30 mins.
Immediately flip over on a cookie sheet.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together in blender, except for gallon of milk.
Pour in churn and finish filling with milk.

title: easy-does-it lasagna
directions: Mix spaghetti sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Set aside.
Mix cottage cheese, onion and egg; set aside.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except apples together with a mixer. Pour half the batter in a greased tube pan.
Put a layer of apples and half the cinnamon-sugar mixture on top. Add remaining batter, apples and cinnamon-sugar mixture.

title: chicken, tomato, onion salad
directions: Place onion in small baking dish.
Sprinkle with Cajun seasoning, vinegar and olive oil.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° until slightly limp.
Cool.
Combine with remaining ingredients and toss.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand for 12 hours before serving.

title: mushroom caps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Chop up mushroom stems. Add onion and butter and cook until tender. Stir in flour, wine, water and pepper. Cook until thick. Add ham and cheese. Stuff mushroom caps with this mixture. Place in shallow baking pan and sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake in preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.

title: mexican meat dish
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Add remaining ingredients, except chips and cheese.
Bring to a good boil.
Pour half of mixture into serving pan.
Add chips and remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: red velvet cake from a mix
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
In large bowl, combine all cake ingredients at low speed until moistened; beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour batter into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched in center.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely.
One sixteenth of recipe equals 500 calories.
Ice with seven minute icing or your favorite icing.

title: time saver corn meal dressing(for 10 to 12 pound turkey)
directions: Combine corn meal and water in a saucepan.
Add butter and cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Combine hot mush with remaining ingredients.
(Use an additional 1/2 cup warm water for more moist stuffing.)

title: quick hamburger supper
directions: Combine beef, onion, bread, 1/2 cup of the water, 1/2 teaspoon of the salt, pepper and nutmeg in a large bowl; mix well.
Shape into 4 loaves.
Cook loaves in hot oil in a large skillet until browned.
Stir in gravy and wine.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes or until cooked through.
Meanwhile, bring remaining water and salt to a boil.
Stir in rice and parsley; cover. Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.
Serve rice with loaves.

title: baked pork chops with rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour rice into a large, greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle onion mix over rice.
Lay pork chops on top of rice mixture.
Pour can of cream of mushroom soup over pork chops.
Add water.
Cover.
Bake for one hour.
Remove cover and brown top a few minutes.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Place half of noodles in a 2-quart casserole.
Combine ham and 3/4 cup of cheese; sprinkle half of ham mixture over noodles.
Combine soup and milk, mixing well.
Pour half of soup mixture over ham mixture.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese; dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix
sticks
melted butter, sugar and eggs.
Add 1/2 cup cocoa
and
mix
well, then add flour and mix well.
Pour into greased
x
9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until done.
Pour package of mini marshmallows evenly over
top. Place in oven just long enough for marshmallows to plump up slightly.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put in saucepan; simmer 15 to 20 minutes, then add to meat (hamburger, pork or beef).

title: pecan pie
directions: Place pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Mix sugar, flour and salt. Set aside.
Beat eggs. Add Karo, oleo and vanilla, then flour mixture.
Pour over pecans.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Reduce temperature to 300° and bake 15 minutes.

title: harris' spotted owl casserole
directions: Toss stuffing mix with 1/2 of soup, broth and eggs.
Spread in casserole and top with owl or chicken.
Combine soup with milk and pour over owl or chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: no-cook irish potato candy
directions: Melt butter and mix with potatoes and confectioners sugar. Knead until smooth.
Roll flat; spread your choice on top.
Roll up into a log.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice thin and serve.

title: barley mushroom soup
directions: Heat oil in a large soup pot over medium heat.
Add vegetables. Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Cover; reduce heat to low and simmer 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings (3/4 cup each).

title: tex-mex tostada soup
directions: Cook meat with onions in 3-quart saucepan. Drain.
Drain and chop the tomatoes and reserve juice.
Add tomatoes and juice to saucepan along with beans, water, bouillon cubes, picante sauce, cumin and oregano. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve topped with tortilla chips and cheese.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease 8 x 8-inch pan.
Slice apples in pan. Sprinkle with water, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Work the rest of the ingredients together for topping.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: parsley buttered new potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and put into a saucepan. Pour in boiling water to 1-inch depth. Add salt; cover and cook about 15 minutes, or until tender. Drain and peel. Return potatoes to saucepan and toss with butter and parsley.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients; set aside. Cream sugar and oil together. Add vanilla and egg yolks, one at a time, mixing well after each one. Mix thoroughly. Add the dry ingredients to oil mixture and mix thoroughly. Add carrots, pineapple and nuts. Mix well. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in 350° oven for 80 minutes. When cool, top with Buttermilk Icing. Great family favorite for the holidays.

title: pork chops and spanish rice
directions: Saute rice in a large skillet in vegetable oil over medium-high heat 3 to 5 minutes or until browned, stirring constantly. Remove rice and set aside.

Add pork chops to skillet. Brown on both sides. Combine rice, tomatoes, green pepper, onion, salt and pepper. Spoon over pork chops. Add water. Cover and simmer 50 to 55 minutes or until pork chops are tender.
Recipe may be doubled for larger servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Place in large bowl the sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla. Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon. Stir until batter is formed. Add pecans, apples and cherries. Stir. Pour into greased and floured angel food cake pan (Bundt). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and crumbs.
Add to milk.
Cook until thick. Add coconut.
Chill.

title: heavenly fruit salad(serves 20 to 30 people)
directions: Combine and cook until mixture coats spoon. Cool! Blend into 1 pint whipped heavy cream, whipped very stiff. Fold into drained fruit. Cover. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: angela pasta with olive oil and garlic
directions: Cooking pasta according to directions on package and drain well. In skillet, heat oil on high heat. Add garlic, salt, and pepper. Stir and cook 4 minutes. Turn off heat. Add hot cooked and well drained pasta to sauce in skillet and toss well. Add tomatoes and basil (or parsley) and toss gently.

title: red beans and rice with sausage
directions: Sort through beans; discard any discolored ones.
Rinse beans; set aside.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla; add egg.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients; blend in mixture.
Chill one hour.
On lightly floured surface, roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in desired shapes.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: baked shrimp tortellini
directions: Cook shrimp, drain and set aside to cool.
Clean.
Add pasta to 5 quarts boiling water.
Boil gently, uncovered, 8 to 9 minutes or until desired tenderness. Drain. Set aside to cool. Combine cleaned and cooked shrimp, pasta and sauce in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix until shrimp and pasta are coated with sauce.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle with cheese evenly over pasta and shrimp. Bake in covered casserole dish for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: fruit medley
directions: Mix
pineapple,
strawberry
filling
and milk in large bowl. Gently fold in Cool Whip, coconut and pecans.

title: goop(not for eating - play substance)
directions: Mix equal parts of cornstarch and water in a large dishpan. Allow children to play in it.
They will enjoy its unusual properties.
And moms, it cleans up easily!!!

title: pink panther salad
directions: Mix well.
Put in large Pyrex dish and refrigerate.

title: cocoa frosting
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add cocoa; heat until smooth, stirring constantly.
Pour into bowl and add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat well and spread on cake.
Suitable for freezing.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Kisses.
Roll into balls. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Press in candy Kisses while still warm.

title: northern italian black meat
directions: Insert cloves at approximately 1 inch intervals over roast. Chop up vegetables.
Put roast and vegetables in roaster.
Cover ingredients with red wine.
Cook for 24 hours at 200°.
Meat will be black and tender.
Remove meat.
Puree remaining ingredients for sauce.

title: broccoli salad mold
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain well. Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold consomme.
Heat remaining consomme to a boil.
Add gelatin mixture and seasonings.
Cool but don't let it gel.
Blend in mayonnaise.
Add chopped eggs and broccoli. Refrigerate.
Yields approximately 7 cups.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan which has been greased with mayonnaise.
Serves 12 (serving about 3 x 3-inch).

title: deep fry okra
directions: Wash and cut okra into thick slices.
Make a batter of eggs, flour and milk.
Add salt.
Put enough flour so it will be kind of thick.
Dip okra into batter, then put into deep fryer.
Cook about 10 minutes or until it is golden brown.

title: easy never fail yeast rolls
directions: Add yeast, eggs, sugar and salt to lukewarm water.
Add 2 cups flour to water mixture and 1/2 cup oil.
Add remaining 4 cups flour, 2 cups at a time.
Grease sides of bowl and top of flour mixture.
Cover and let rise 2 hours (should double in size). Punch down.
Roll out on floured surface, about 1-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise for 2 more hours.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beefy broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil in medium saucepan. Add broccoli and onion; cook 5 minutes or until broccoli is tender.

title: grandma's baked lima beans
directions: Cook dry lima beans with ham until almost done.
Combine with sugar and catsup and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: artichoke and cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into a 2 to 3-inch deep baking dish. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: southwestern chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken
up
into
1-inch chunks and toss with oil, lime juice and cayenne pepper.
Salt and pepper is optional to taste. Spoon mixture
into a pan and bake for 15 minutes in a preheated oven
at
until
chicken is cooked.
Drain and cool.
Add the rest of the ingredients.

title: coconut pecan
directions: Mix the cake mix, water, oil, and eggs together.
Add frosting by hand whipping into above mixture.
Pour into Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45-60 minutes.

title: diabetic fruit cocktail whip
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice and saccharin.
Chill until mixture begins to set.
Beat until fluffy; fold in fruit cocktail.
Chill until firm.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat well.
Pour in uncooked pie shell and cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pecans.
Bring mixture to a boil in a stainless steel frying pan.
Once mixture begins to boil, add pecans and stir continuously until pecans soak up water and cinnamon.
Pour out onto waxed paper on table top and separate pecans until cool.

title: delicious pea salad
directions: Mix peas, bacon pieces, eggs, onion and salad dressing. Spread on top of shredded lettuce and sprinkle with cheese.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles.
Layer tuna and soup alternately with noodles in casserole.
Season.
Crush potato chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix first ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes stirring often.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Mix well. Pour over popped popcorn and peanuts; mix with a wooden spoon. Place in a flat pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Take from oven and store in airtight container after cool.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Use your hands and form small balls.
Chill at least 24 hours with toothpick in center for dipping.
Dip in Candi-quick chocolate (1 1/2 packages chocolate).
Yields 6 dozen.

title: old fashioned chocolate fudge
directions: Grease a loaf pan. (Use butter or oleo.) Combine sugar, milk, chocolate,	corn
syrup and salt in a 2-quart saucepan. Cook
over medium heat, stirring constantly until chocolate is melted	and sugar is dissolved.
Cook, stirring occasionally, to 234° on candy thermometer (or until small amount of mixture dropped
into very cold water forms a soft ball which flattens when removed from water).
Remove from heat; add butter.
Cool mixture
to
120° without
stirring,	(bottom
of pan will be lukewarm).
Add vanilla
and beat vigorously and continuously for 5
to
10 minutes with wooden spoon, until candy is thick and
no longer glossy.
Spread evenly in a buttered pan.
Cool until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: easy mexican chicken
directions: Saute pepper and onion in oil until tender-crisp.
Add chicken; cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is no longer pink (8 to 10 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil. Cover, lower heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, let stand 5 minutes and stir.
Add cheese to cover top of chicken. Replace lid; let stand until cheese has melted.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until moistened.
Do not heat.
Stir in pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter in 3 greased and floured pans or 1 (13 x 9-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: halibut and sausage(from a friend, hyme andrews)
directions: Serves 6 to
Actually,
I
decide how much fish and sausage I need by number of people.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°. Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press into 9-inch spring-form pan. In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until smooth. Beat in eggs and lemon juice. Pour into prepared pan. Bake 50 minutes or until center is set. Top with sour cream. Bake 5 minutes. Cool. Chill.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Salt and flour chicken.
Brown lightly quickly.
Do not cook done.
Drain grease.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover tightly. Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender. Serve over spaghetti.

title: blue ridge mountain corn bread
directions: In separate bowls, beat the egg whites and egg yolks.
To the egg yolks, add the sugar and beat well.
Add the cornmeal, milk and flour.
Add the melted butter, beaten egg whites and baking powder. Then pour into a greased pan.
Bake in a 450° oven until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt 2 tablespoons bacon grease in 8 x 8-inch pan.
After mixing all ingredients, add touch of the melted bacon grease.
Mix thoroughly and pour into 8 x 8-inch preheated pan and bake about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy red beans and rice
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper, garlic and ham in the olive oil until onions are clear.
Add seasoning and stir.
Add beans.
Stir constantly and bring to gentle boil.
Reduce to low heat and cook for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
The red beans freeze well.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute pepper and celery in margarine.
Add flour, soup and milk.
Mix well.
Add carrots and pimientos.
Spread potatoes in long baking dish and pour mixture over them.
Add 3/4 of the cheese.
Cook 25 minutes at 400°, then add remainder of cheese on top.
Bake 5 more minutes or until cheese melts.

title: green salad
directions: Mix jello, cream cheese and hot water.
When well mixed, add marshmallows.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
Remove from refrigerator and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Pour over berries.
Add to pie shell; dot with butter and cover with top crust.
Bake at 450° for ten minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: tomato and cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour.
Cook over low heat for
one minute.
Stir in 1 cup milk; cook until thick.
Stir in second cup of milk, tomato paste, oregano and salt.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in cheeses.

title: mock chicken fried steak
directions: Combine egg, 1/2 cracker crumbs, milk, onion, chili powder, salt and sauce.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Shape into patties.
Coat patties with rest of cracker crumbs.
Cook in hot oil on medium heat about 3 minutes on each side.

title: aunt emmie's chicken picase(serves 2)
directions: Beat egg with milk in a medium-size bowl.
Set aside.
In a shallow dish, add salt, pepper, parsley and flour; mix.
Dip cutlet into flour mixture and then coat with beaten egg.

title: toll house pie
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Mix in flour and sugar until blended.
Blend in butter; mix in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour in pie shell and bake about 1 hour or until set.

title: zesty potato salad
directions: Boil the potatoes.
Let cool, peel and dice in small chunks. Add the remaining ingredients to taste.

title: pie dough
directions: Combine the flour, sugar, salt and lard.
Knead, then add the cold water.
Makes 4 pie shells.

title: stuffed pumpkin
directions: Pumpkin:
Cut top out of pumpkin, about 5 to 6-inches across (save lid).
Seed and scrape the insides of the pumpkin.
Combine salt, pepper and sugar in a small cup and sprinkle to coat inside of pumpkin.
Place pumpkin in a sturdy broiler pan.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in egg.
Sift together the remaining ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.

title: ham potato patties
directions: Combine the potatoes, onion and ham.
Chill for one hour. Shape this cooled mixture into 16 to 18 patties.
Combine the milk and egg.
Dip the patties into this mixture and then in the bread crumbs.
Fry the patties in hot oil until golden brown.

title: frank-a-bobs(method:  stick)
directions: Cut hot dogs into pieces; thread pieces of meat and desired vegetables onto sticks to cook over coals.
When desired cooking time has passed for individuals, place cooked food into hot dog roll and add preferred condiments.

title: easy cream-style corn
directions: Mix all together; warm over medium heat until bubbly and thick.

title: sweet spiced gherkins
directions: Scrub cucumbers with a brush, then soak for 24 hours in brine made of salt and 3 cups water.
Remove from brine and pour boiling water over.
Drain quickly.
Pack cucumbers closely, while hot, in sterilized jars.
Cover at once with boiling mixture made from vinegar, 1 pint water, sugar substitute and spices.
Seal jars at once.
Makes about 5 pints.
Contains 40 calories per pint.

title: elizabeth's gingerbread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients. Cut in butter to make crumb mixture. Take out 1 cup crumbs and set aside. Add molasses, buttermilk and eggs. Mix well and pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture on top. Bake at 25 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: bill's gehenna hot sauce
directions: Scald and peel tomatoes.
(Put whole tomatoes in boiling water for 2 minutes; plunge into cold water and remove skins.)
Then chop in blender.
Grind onions, green pepper and jalapeno peppers with coarse blade of food chopper.
Cook all ingredients 30 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine in bowl and you are set to go!

title: shrimp custard
directions: Drain canned shrimp and rinse with cold water.
Cut large shrimp in half.
Remove crusts from bread and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place half the bread cubes in a well-greased baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Cover with a layer of shrimp, green pepper and half the cheese.
Top with remaining bread cubes and cheese. Combine eggs, mustard, salt and pepper; beat.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour over bread; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 45 to 50 minutes, or until firm in the center. Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
In large bowl, combine all bar ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into prepared pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Bake as directed on package.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Put in double boiler, egg white, sugar and water. Place over boiling water and beat with mixer for 7 minutes. Add baking powder and flavorings. Remove from heat. Beat until thick then spread on cake.

title: estelle's instant banana pudding
directions: Crush enough wafers to generously cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat pudding and milk.
Fold in sour cream and half of the Cool Whip.
Slice 3 bananas over the wafers layer.
Spread half of pudding mix and repeat layers; wafers, bananas, pudding and top with rest of the Cool Whip.
The Cool Whip seals it and keeps it from running over.
Refrigerate.
It can not be cut in squares but must be spooned up.
Serves 12.

title: french dip sandwiches
directions: Brown onion and mushroom.
Slice kaiser rolls and butter, then brown in skillet.
Heat roast beef.
Put Swiss cheese on top; cover until cheese has melted.
Make au jus sauce as directed on package.
Put roast beef, cheese with onions and mushrooms on rolls.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo or butter.
Add soup and mushrooms. Cook the spaghetti in chicken stock saved from boiling the chicken.
Combine all ingredients and put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into small pieces.
Add onion and salt. Boil until tender and drain.
Now add eggs, pimientos and margarine to this mixture. (Can beat in mixer or blender.) Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Make a layer of the squash mixture and then cheese and crackers.
(You can also mix all of this together.) Put squash on the top layer. When it begins to brown, put a covering of cheese and sprinkle with cracker crumbs. Bake 10 minutes more.

title: sweet and sour poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let blend.

title: blackened fish fillets(serving size:  6.  preparation time:  0:20)
directions: Mix dry ingredients on large plate.
Melt butter in heavy skillet (do not use light weight or nonstick skillet).
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons into 9 x 12 x 1-inch pan.
Turn on hood vent and turn heat to high.
Dip each fillet in melted butter (in the 9 x 12-inch pan) and then dip in the dry ingredients, patting the fillets by hand.
Cook fish on each side for 2 to 3 minutes, being careful when turning them over.
The fish will look charred "blackened" and there may be some smoke, but not an excessive amount.
The blackening seals forming a spicy, crunchy coating, sealing in moisture and flavor.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 3-quart long baking dish. Boil water and salt; gradually add grits. Cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Gradually add grits to beaten eggs. Return to saucepan. Add sausage, cheese, milk and margarine. Blend well and pour into baking dish. Bake 1 hour.

title: bacon and lettuce stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut the top off of each tomato.
Scoop out pulp and seeds. Salt inside of each tomato.
Invert tomatoes and drain 15 minutes.

title: cheddar potato slices
directions: In small bowl, combine soup, paprika and pepper.
In greased 2 qt. baking dish, arrange potatoes in overlapping rows.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Spoon soup mixture over cheese.
Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla and mix well.
Add dry ingredients gradually and then the pineapple.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet. Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix and spread on top.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cook until thick (mixture will decrease to almost half).
Put in hot jars and seal.
Delicious in meat loaf, spaghetti, baked beans, etc.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts in top of double boiler. Place over simmering water and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix again. Spread candy quickly in buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Most important part to mixing these cookies is to beat oleo and sugar at high speed for 10 minutes.
Very important.
Dissolve soda in vinegar.
Mix with flour and vanilla, then nuts, if desired.
Drop by spoon and bake at 275° for 30 minutes.

title: super spam cheeseball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans and crackers.
Mix well and form into a ball.
Roll in nuts.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 6.

title: chili tortilla roll-ups
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature.
Blend in sour cream.
Add onion, chili and pimientos and stir into mixture.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll tortilla, closing ends as you roll.
Chill.
To serve, cut into 3/4-inch slices or size desired.

title: easy homemade strawberry jam
directions: Stir strawberries and sugar together, mixing thoroughly.
Set aside.
Stir Sure-Jell and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir mixtures together until sugar is completely dissolved and no longer grainy.
Pour into containers.
Cover.
Let stand overnight.
Store in jars in freezer until opened, then store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 (8 ounce) jars.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together and pat into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Make sure the layer is thin. Bake at 350° until light brown, about 15 to 20 minutes. In a heavy saucepan, cook and stir the sweetened condensed milk, salt and oleo until oleo melts; then cook and stir over medium heat for 5 minutes. It will be thick and smooth. Stir in vanilla. Spread over baked layer. Bake at 350° until golden, about 12 to 15 minutes. It will be bubbly. Spread warm cookies with Fudge Frosting (see recipe following) and cut into bars while warm. Remove from pan.

title: fried potatoes
directions: In frying pan, cook meat until crisp; remove and set aside.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems and finely chop.
In a medium skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of the corn oil over medium heat.
Add stems, onion and pepper.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes; stir frequently.
Stir in bread crumbs and cream cheese; mix well.
Brush mushroom caps on both sides with remaining corn oil.
Place hollow-side up in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Fill each with cheese mixture.
Bake in 375° oven 10 to 15 minutes or until heated.

title: hot spicy meat balls(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Mix in a bowl all ingredients.

title: pierogi
directions: Peel and cook 4 to 6 potatoes as for mashing.
Mash with 1 tablespoon margarine and 1/2 pound Cheddar cheese; let cool.
Make a dough with 2 1/2 cups flour, 1 egg and enough water to make a dough; pinch off small pieces of dough and roll out.
Fill with potato mixture; fold dough over and pinch edges.
Continue this until all potatoes are used.
You can either fry them in hot oil or boil them.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast
in
water and set aside.
Combine cottage cheese, onion, dill
weed,
soda,
sugar, butter and salt. Mix egg with yeast
and
combine all using electric mixer; beat in flour. Knead and
let rise until doubled in size.
Stir dough down and knead
again.
Turn
into well-greased 8-inch round 2 quart casserole, let rise
again.
Bake
at
350° for 40 to 45 minutes until brown.
Brush with additional soft butter.

title: mr. food's great, great pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Mix pudding mix with milk and half and half.
When thickened, add Dream Whip.
Put half of fruit mix in pie shell; add pudding mix and top with remaining fruit.
Chill before serving.
Ooh, it's so good.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry jello; add pineapple (juice and all).
Add Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving (5 to 6 hours).

title: spicy carrot bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine first four dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and mix with the next six ingredients.
Add carrots and mix all together until moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased loaf (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) pans.
Preheat oven to 325° and bake for 60 to 70 minutes.
Insert toothpick until it comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.

title: fruit salad dessert
directions: Cut cantaloupe up. Oranges need to be cut so the peel and pulp can be removed. Mix the fruit and let stand to juice.

title: poppy seed and nut rolls
directions: Mix the top 3 ingredients together, beat until lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water and set aside. Mix well. Put in fridge until cold for about 2 hours or until you want (overnight).

title: two sweet potato pies
directions: Beat potatoes until smooth.
Mix potatoes with cinnamon, vanilla, butter, eggs, flour and sugar.
Pour mixture into pie shells.
Cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sausage stew
directions: Heat the oil in a heavy pan and add the onion, garlic, celery, fennel, salt and pepper.
Saute until soft.
Add all other ingredients except for the sausage and cook for 20 minutes over low heat.
Add sausage; simmer for another 15 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: pancake mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in refrigerator.

title: red potato salad
directions: While still warm cut unpeeled potatoes into 1 inch cubes. Gently toss together potatoes, onions and salad dressing.
Dust with paprika or pepper.
Garnish with fresh chives.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: almond joy cookies
directions: Heat over double boiler, milk and chocolate.
Mix coconut with chocolate mixture, than add vanilla and salt.
Drop on waxed paper on cookie sheet (greased) by tablespoonful.
Add one almond on top of each one.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, but check at 8 to 9 minutes and keep checking until done.
Do not overbake.

title: noodles and tomatoes
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Add cream of mushroom soup, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring often.

title: chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate kisses.
Roll into balls and roll in white sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 375°.
While hot, place 1 chocolate kiss into center.

title: apple yams
directions: Bake sweet potatoes.
Pierce skin and allow 40 to 60 minutes at 400° or cook covered in boiling water to cover for 30 to 35 minutes until tender.
Drain and cool and remove skin.
Grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Alternate layers of sweet potatoes and apples, sprinkling each layer with cinnamon, brown sugar and butter.
Top layer should be apples.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 45 minutes.

title: scotch barley soup
directions: Saut in oil, onion and garlic.
Add flour to make roux (paste).
Cook flour roux for 10 minutes; add chicken stock and bring to a boil.
Add ground lamb and cook 15 minutes.
Add precooked barley and bring to a high simmer. Add turnip (or potato), carrots, celery and milk.
Add salt, pepper and basil until vegetables are tender.
May need to add more milk for a creamier soup or chicken stock to thin it out.

title: yakamein
directions: There should never a recipe book originate in our area unless several recipes are given for the use of one of the greatest delicacies in all the world, because they grow best right here in the great state of West Virginia.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Skin tomatoes and cut in quarters.
Halve pepper; seed and slice into strips.
Slice onion into thin rings.
Arrange vegetables in a large baking dish (not metal) or you can mix them all together in a large bowl.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix and roll out for pie pan.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Combine water, orange juice, lemonade and limeade in punch bowl until well blended.
Before serving, add soda, sherbet scoops and ice cubes.
Fruited ice cubes are just ice cubes with various fruits (cherries, raspberries, blueberries, orange sections, etc.) frozen inside them.

title: nacho appetizer
directions: Spread refried beans over platter. Mix salsa and sour cream. Spread over beans.
Layer with green onions, black olives, cheese and tomatoes.
Serve with chips.
Serves 12 as appetizer.

title: black beans
directions: Wash and soak black beans overnight.
Drain and add fresh water about 5 inches over beans.
Add finely chopped onion, bell pepper and garlic, olive oil, oregano, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat slowly so no added water is necessary. Great as soup or goes well with picadilo and yellow rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add alternately and top with crushed potato chips or bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, then remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off green peppers; remove seeds and membrane.
Cook peppers in enough boiling water to cover for 5 minutes; drain.
In medium skillet on range top, cook and stir ground beef and onion until onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in rice, salt, pepper and garlic.
Divide evenly into peppers.
Arrange peppers upright in dish.
Blend soup and water until smooth; pour over peppers. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Re-cover; let stand 5 to 10 minutes to melt cheese.

title: mix-ahead meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pack into a loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate easter eggs
directions: Melt Baker's chocolate in top of double boiler, then set aside to cool.
Mix together butter, mashed potatoes, salt and vanilla. Gradually add sugar, then add chocolate.
Form into shape of 2 eggs.
Melt semi-sweet chocolate in double boiler and cover eggs. Refrigerate until chocolate hardens.

title: jane's fudge
directions: In a very large bowl, empty morsels and marshmallows.
Add vanilla and softened butter.
Set aside.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth. Bake in a 9 x 13 inch pan at 375° for 50 minutes, or until golden brown. No need to ice, just serve with butter.

title: chicken cheese dip
directions: Combine all this.
Melt together; stir well.
Ready to serve.

title: cabbage patch cole slaw(salad)
directions: Combine vegetables.
Blend remaining ingredients, stirring to dissolve.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss.
Tastes best the next day!

title: reception punch
directions: Mix all juices and water together.
Dissolve sugar in an additional 2 cups of boiling water; add to juices.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Float slices of lemon and orange on the top.
Makes 70 cups.

title: yellow squash pickles
directions: Combine squash, onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand 1 hour.
Combine vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to boil.
Add squash, onion and green pepper and return to boil.
Pack in hot, sterilized jars, covering with vinegar mixture.
Seal.
Yields 4 pints.

title: louisiana best steak marinade
directions: Combine all, mixing well.
Put in container with a top.
Shake well.
Pour over steaks.
Marinate for 3 to 4 hours.
Grill or broil steaks.
This is the best!
It also tenderizes as it marinates.

title: carrot and apple dish
directions: Cook carrots until tender. Season with Crisco and salt. Mix carrots, drained, sugar, cinnamon and apple pie filling. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: christmas cider
directions: Simmer lemon for 10 minutes.
In 8-ounce cup, squeeze lemon; add 1 ounce glycerin.
Fill to 8 ounces with honey.
Stir.
Take as necessary.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix together.
Add enough cracker crumbs to make patties.
Fry in hot oil until crisp (just a few minutes on each side).

title: pecan bars
directions: Combine flour, 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 1/2 cup softened margarine.
Press mix into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool and cut into bars or squares.

title: chicken nut bites
directions: In saucepan, combine chicken broth and margarine; bring to boiling.
Stir in flour, parsley, seasoned salt, celery seed, Worcestershire sauce, paprika and cayenne.
Cook, beating rapidly until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a smooth, compact ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition until mixture is shiny.
Stir in chicken and almonds.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 18 minutes or until browned.
Serve hot.
Makes 75 puffs.

title: no-cook cake icing
directions: Beat 1 cup 10-X sugar and egg white together until smooth. Then add all remaining ingredients and beat well.
If desired, add food coloring of choice and ice cake.

title: pepperoni puffs
directions: Combine all of ingredients.
Spoon into greased miniature size muffin pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen puffs.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Brown beef and drain.
In a separate bowl, combine picante sauce, water and tomato sauce.
Stir 1/2 cup of sauces into browned beef along with chilies, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup French fried onions.
Mix well.
Pour half of remaining sauce mixture on bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Stuff cooked shells with ground beef mixture.
Arrange shells in baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and French fried onions.
Bake uncovered for 5 more minutes.

title: yellow pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan or tube pan.
Mix cake, pudding, eggs, water and oil in large bowl.
Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted in center.

title: strawberry salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: Wash lettuce and pat dry. Place greens on individual salad plates. Arrange strawberries and onions on top of the greens.

title: my sister's chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice peppers and mushrooms.
Place chicken breasts in oblong baking dish and season as desired. Place sliced vegetables and onions around chicken.
Mix dressing and pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake until done, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.
Best served with wild rice or dressing.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: In medium-sized baking dish (1 1/2 to 2-quart), combine all ingredients; sprinkle top with butter and Ritz cracker crumbs to cover.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Combine ingredients and mix according to directions on back of cake mix box.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Prepare glaze of powdered sugar and orange juice.
Dribble over warm cake.
Garnish with lemon slices, if desired.

title: kuchen
directions: Mix 1 cup of the flour with sugar, salt, yeast, margarine and water; beat 2 minutes.
Add 4 eggs and 1 cup of flour and beat 2 more minutes.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Stir in lemon peel, nutmeg and 1 to 2 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan.
Cover and let rise in warm place.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend cream cheese until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Chill.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken (save broth).
Remove chicken from bone.
Mix chicken and dressing together.
Cook seasoning package in butter until soft.
Add to chicken; mix well.
Add soups and mix well. Add broth to make moist.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: easy southern biscuits
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the oil and milk.
Blend together.
Flour a bread board and knead the dough until it holds together.
Roll out to thickness desired and cut with biscuit cutter.
Put on a greased pan and bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: creamed sweet potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes; add margarine, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add raisins.
Beat with mixer to mix well; add 1 small can of milk. Pour in a well-greased Corning Ware dish.
Bake about 45 minutes at 450°. when done, cover potatoes with large marshmallows and return to stove and brown.

title: french toast
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 pan. Slice bread thick and put in pan. Beat all ingredients except butter and pour over bread. Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight. Lay butter on top and bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sauteed green beans
directions: Put green beans, chicken bouillon, chervil and salt into saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until crisp-tender. (For frozen beans, cook 6 to 8 minutes.)
Drain thoroughly.

title: sinfully delicious
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions.
Poke holes in brownies with a fork.
Pour Kahlua liqueur over top of brownies and set aside and cool.
Make chocolate mousse according to package directions.
Break candy into small pieces.
Place 1/2 soaked and crumbled brownies in bottom of trifle dish.
Cover with 1/2 of mousse mixture.
Top with 1/2 of candy bits.
Top with 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Repeat.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter
and powdered sugar.
Mix all ingredients, adding one egg at a
time	until 5 eggs have been added.
Beat well.
Put in a tube or Bundt pan.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple-winter squash mash
directions: Peel, cube and steam for 20 minutes and then mash.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese and sugar together.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add milk and mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put into graham cracker crust and freeze overnight.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Add pudding mix to milk; beat until well blended (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk. Spread over whipped cream layer.
Refrigerate minimum of 3 hours. Can add additional whipped topping or nuts, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Mix all together (allow cheese to soften first).
You may mold into balls or leave in bowl.

title: monkey bread
directions: Make dough according to Bisquick package directions.
Roll dough into small balls.
Pour melted butter, sugar and cinnamon over dough.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pineapple.
Fold in the bread cubes.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
This is great with ham.

title: dilly snackin' crackers
directions: Mix oil and dry ingredients in a shaker.
Put crackers in a large flat pan.
Pour oil mixture over them; stir well.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese and Cheddar cheese soften at room temperature. Add remaining ingredients.

title: rhayne's fruit pizza
directions: Mix (add water to juices to make a full cup).
Heat until thick.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in sugar, melted oleo and flour to which cocoa has been added.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Bake in greased, floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 35 minutes. Remove from oven; cover with large marshmallows (cut in half), placing cut side down.
Cover with chocolate icing.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: strawberry shortcake with strawberry glaze
directions: Boil until thick.
Mix with strawberries and spread over yellow cake.

title: mammies ice cream pie
directions: Mix vanilla pudding, chocolate pudding and milk; mix well. Add vanilla ice cream.
Pour into baked pie shell and frost with Dream Whip (made according to directions).
Chill.
Makes 1 pie.

title: no bake chocolate cheesecake
directions: Boil 1/2 cup milk, take off heat and pour into blender.
Add gelatine; blend.
Add 1/2 cup milk, egg yolks, cocoa, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla.
Blend at medium speed until well blended.

title: golden fish puffs
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place fillets in a greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish; season with salt and pepper.
Beat egg white and 1/8 teaspoon salt until stiff but not dry.
Fold in remaining ingredients; spoon onto fish.
Bake, uncovered, 12 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork and topping is puffed and brown.

title: baked custard
directions: Mix and pour into custard
cups or Pyrex bowl.
Place in a cake pan that has about 1/2-inch boiling water in it.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.

title: rolls
directions: Heat milk, sugar and shortening until shortening melts, cool. Dissolve yeast in water.
Add to cooled first mixture.
Add flour to mixture and mix with a rotary beater.
Allow to rise until double (about an hour).
Stir down and add remaining ingredients and enough flour to make it the consistency of biscuit dough. Shape rolls and dip in melted butter.
Place in greased pan and allow to rise 2 hours.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mash strawberries with sugar.
Let stand 1 hour.
Force through strainer.
Add orange and lemon juices, ginger ale and 1/2 cup sugar to strained strawberry juice.
Pour into large punch bowl.
Add sliced strawberries.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: beef rice bake
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add soup and water, diced celery and green pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Pour into Pam sprayed casserole dish. Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serve with bran muffins and salad or muffins of your choice.
Do not add salt.

title: archbishop's punch
directions: Stick cloves in the mandarins and roast in a warm oven, about 250°, until skin is brown.
When skin is brown, take out of oven, cut into quarters and put in a saucepan, cover with Claret or Burgundy.
Add sugar and let simmer until hot.
Strain.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend milk into cream cheese.
Add confectioners sugar to cream cheese.
Spread on pie shell.
Cover with whole fresh strawberries.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Stir until blended.
Add 1 pint strawberries, cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Mix in food coloring in pie shell.
Decorate with whipped cream.

title: hamburger skillet
directions: Fry hamburger.
Add bread and seasonings until browned (do not stir after adding the following).
Layer corn and onions.
Cover with tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Do not stir; cover.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: baklava
directions: Thaw pastry and separate into thirds.
Place 1/3 in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Brush sheet with melted butter.
Combine nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle 1/2 over buttered pastry; repeat 1/3 dough and butter each sheet.
Cut into 2 inch diamonds.
Bake at 400° until brown and crisp, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple nut tea sandwiches(brunch, lunch or high tea)
directions: In saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil. Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Cool. Stir in nuts.
Soften and mash cheese with enough milk or mayonnaise to make a good spreading consistency.
Combine with pineapple mixture.
Spread on thin bread.
Trim and cut into squares.
Makes 4 cups.

title: brewers b b q sauce
directions: 1. Melt butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat. 2. Add onion and cook for about 2 minutes.
Add garlic and cook 3 more minutes. 3. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: drizzle topped brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
In medium bowl combine baking mix, sugar and cocoa; mix with spoon or fork until blended.
Add butter, eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread into pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: brownies
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg whites, oil and brown sugar until smooth.
Add yogurt and vanilla.
Beat again.
Add flour, cocoa and salt.
Beat until well-mixed.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup and milk.
Layer in casserole dish in following order: 1/3 cup soup mixture, 1/2 eggs, 1/2 cheese, all the eggplant and other 1/2 eggs and cheese.
Cover with rest of the soup mixture.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven until brown and bubbly.

title: creamy lemonade pie
directions: In mixing bowl combine pudding mix and evaporated milk.
Beat on low speed for 2 minutes.
Mixture will be thick.

title: orange pecan pie
directions: Spread with tips of fingers just enough of egg mixture on bottom and sides of pie shell to coat it.
Place in oven for 5 minutes at 425°; this prevents a soggy crust.
Add to rest of egg mixture the rest of the ingredients.
Mix and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Test with knife for doneness.

title: pineapple cream cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix per directions on box.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut bread sticks
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Cut each slice into 4 or 5 sticks. Bake sticks and crusts for 45 minutes at 250°.
Heat oil and peanut butter.
Keep on low.
Dip sticks into oil mixture and roll in mixture of bread crumbs (made from toasted crust) and sesame seed.

title: baptist salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple and let stand a few minutes; add Cool Whip and nuts.
(Add marshmallows, if desired).

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Heat until smooth chicken soup and milk.
Brown ground beef and drain.
In 8 x 8-inch baking dish, alternate sauce mixture, beef and tortillas.
You may tear tortillas as you place in layers; use sauce last.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lazy man cookie bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar, flavoring and egg yolk.
Stir in flour and cinnamon until smooth.
(The dough is very stiff.)
Pat out on greased jelly roll pan.
Brush top with beaten egg white and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in bars at once and remove from pan.

title: swedish shortbread(colored cookies)
directions: Blend butter or margarine and powdered sugar. Add egg and vanilla.
Add flour.
Divide into 3 portions. Add food coloring to 2 portions.
Press out with cookie press.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375° or until slightly browned.

title: cheese drop biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in butter, then add cheese.
Pour milk into mixture slowly (might need a little less).
Drop dough from tablespoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 450° (or until lightly browned).

title: ann's red velvet cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, vinegar and cake coloring together.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Use 2 greased and floured cake pans.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Slice stem ends from green peppers; scoop out seeds.
Blanch in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine ground beef, egg, salt, rice, 57 sauce, half of the barbecue sauce and onion.
Fill peppers; place in saucepan.
Combine remaining barbecue sauce, tomato juice and sugar; pour over peppers.
Bring to a boil. Simmer, covered, for 40 to 60 minutes.
Baste occasionally. Serves 6.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, cool slightly, peel and dice. Saute onions in margarine.
Add onion mixture to potatoes along with the rest of ingredients.
Pour mixture into 12 x 8-inch casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken creole soup
directions: This is a big commercial recipe that makes a lot.
Mix all ingredients; simmer and serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients; pour into deep casserole dish.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle in a layer each of graham crackers, coconut, chocolate pieces and nuts.
Pour condensed milk over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Makes 16 squares.

title: pepperoni bites
directions: For filling, in a bowl, combine Mozzarella cheese, pepperoni and pizza sauce.
Set aside.
Separate biscuits.
Flatten biscuits to 3-inch circles.
Place 1 rounded tablespoonful of filling in the center of each circle.
Bring edges of dough together.
Pinch to seal.
Place, seam side down, on greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Serve warm. Makes 20.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Use tablespoon of dough for each cookie.
Bake on greased pan.
Sprinkle with plain or colored sugar before baking. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: crisp waffles
directions: Add first 4 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Then add egg yolks, milk and oil; beat until creamy smooth.
Beat egg whites (in a separate bowl) until stiff.
Fold into first mixture.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in pan the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Put on medium heat; cook until it starts to boil.
Remove from heat; cool for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, salt and oats; stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: jello pie
directions: Combine Jell-O with 1 cup water.
Let Jell-O cool.
Prepare pie pan (large).
Rub unsalted margarine on pie pan (bottom and sides).
Beat cold evaporated milk and add Jell-O, a little at a time.
Add sugar and rind.
Beat until fluffy.

title: candied orange peel
directions: Cut peel of oranges into 4 sections with sharp knife.
Remove peel carefully with fingers.
Scrape white membrane from peel with spoon.
Cut peel lengthwise into strips 1/4-inch wide.
Heat peel and 8 cups water to boiling in a 3-quart saucepan.
Reduce heat. Heat, simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Drain.
Heat 2 cups sugar and 1 cup water to boiling in a 2-quart saucepan, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Add peel; simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 45 minutes.
Drain in strainer.
Roll peel in 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Spread on wax paper to dry.

title: corn cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together. Add rest of ingredients. Stir together. Grease 9 x 9-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crab mousse
directions: Grease mold.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.

title: ice cream balls
directions: Make ice cream balls.
Roll in preceding mixture.
Serve with hot fudge.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Tender chicken in water with seasonings.
Debone.
Cook with vermicelli in broth.
Melt Velveeta; saute onions and bell peppers in margarine.
Add soups, pimento, peas, mushrooms, Ro-Tel and cheese.
Mix in vermicelli and cheese sauce together with enough broth to make soupy.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Makes 2 large 9 x 13-inch pans.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Cream well:
milk, margarine and sugar.
Cook on High for 8 minutes (I stop it twice to stir).
Remove and add chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Then add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased glass dish or pan.
Refrigerate.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Peel a banana.
Stick peanuts in the sides and sprinkle with carob powder. Eat!

title: elegant meat balls
directions: Form small meat balls with the beef, onion, carrot, egg, water and bread crumbs.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Place meat balls on sheet and cook at 400° for 20 minutes.
Simmer cranberry sauce with chili sauce.
Add meat balls and simmer, covered, in oven for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions (drain well). Add soup, mayonnaise, eggs, milk, onions and 1/2 cup cheese; mix well.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Top with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Mix melted oleo with the stuffing; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Extra good!

title: potato soup
directions: Cover all with water and cook until tender.
Fry 8 slices of bacon.
Save 6 tablespoons of drippings and make white sauce.
Add white sauce to soup.
Crumble bacon and add.
Heat thoroughly.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Add corn syrup and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves. Continue cooking, stirring constantly to soft boil stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, oats, coconut and peanuts. Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Saute onion in butter (not browned).
Add hamburger and fry. (Does not have to be browned.)
Add all other ingredients and simmer about 1 hour or until tender.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually beat in sugar until meringue will stand in soft peaks.
Mix crumbs, dates and nuts together.
Add baking powder.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into a 9-inch buttered and floured pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and serve with unsweetened whipped cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef roast
directions: Place roast on large sheet of aluminum foil.
Spread steak sauce over roast.
Sprinkle with dry soup mix, salt and pepper. Pour mushroom soup over the top.
Fold foil to seal tightly.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours and 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Measure butter and soda; mix.
Add vanilla, then the sugar, gradually creaming thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, until mixed.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add pecans.
Bake at 325° for about one hour.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Mix catsup, brown sugar, liquid smoke, garlic powder and onion powder.
Cut ribs into single pieces.
Broil each side 15 minutes. Place in crock-pot.
Cover with sauce.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours.
(High temperature is too hot.
It burns the sauce and ribs.)

title: ham rolls
directions: Pat the ham dry with paper towels.
Spread the cream cheese on the top of the ham.
Sprinkle with chives.
Roll tight.
Slice into chunks.
Serve cold.

title: peanut buster parfait cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine the chocolate cake mix, melted butter, 1/2 cup of the milk, the egg and 3/4 cup of the peanuts; mix at medium speed until well blended.
Spread the mixture evenly into the prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, being careful not to overbake.
Remove from oven to cool.

title: dirt cake
directions: To bright the rainiest day, make cupcake cones with your children.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix
dry ingredients together.
Add onion, then buttermilk and finally
a
beaten
egg.
Drop by spoonfuls into the pan, in which fish have been fried.
Fry to a golden brown and drain.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Grate all the orange peel into a small bowl.
Put the cranberries and the fruit pulp through a food chopper, grinder or blender.
Mix sugar into orange cranberry mixture.
Add grated orange peel.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate until cold.
Delicious served with turkey or chicken.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mash cranberry sauce and add Cool Whip.
Then mash bananas well.
Add to Cool Whip mixture.
Then add well drained pineapple. Put in square dish or pan and leave in freezer overnight.

title: sausage brunch casserole
directions: Prepare evening before.
Cook sausage and drain thoroughly. Beat the eggs and milk slightly.
Add sausage, cubed bread and cheese.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch or 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole and cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until firm in a preheated 350° oven.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello.
Add thawed berries.
Pour on top of cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.
This is so good!

title: salmon cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients except nuts and parsley (by hand, not in a blender).
Form a ball. Roll in crushed nuts and parsley. Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook onion, garlic and butter until soft. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chilies and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Soften corn tortillas in hot oil until soft; drain on paper towel.
Stuff each tortilla with 2 to 3 strips of chicken, 2 teaspoons cheese and 1 tablespoon sauce.
Roll tortilla and place seam side down in greased baking dish.
Mix sour cream into remaining sauce and pour over enchiladas.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pasta pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add garlic, salt and pepper.
Drain grease.
Add Ragu and simmer all for 20 minutes.
Separately cook the rotini per box instructions.
Drain and then pour into the hamburger mixture.	Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13 pan and then add the cheese on top, followed by covering the mixture with the pepperoni slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carol's fantastic taco dip
directions: Put in layers on large round pan:

title: spice cake
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes, then chill.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours or until done.
I use a loaf pan.

title: ambrosia parfait
directions: Beat pudding mix and milk with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes.
Mix in 1/2 c. marshmallows, the banana and pineapple with juice.
Spoon some of mixture into parfait glasses.
Add a layer of the remaining ingredients, alternate with layers of pudding.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter in a large bowl on medium speed until smooth.
Beat in powdered sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.

title: seven in one dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Place in bottom of large baking dish.
Layer carrots, celery and peas next and top with potatoes. Cover with a layer of uncooked noodles and pour tomatoes over all. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° until done. (If more liquid is needed, use tomatoes, tomato juice or water, as desired.) Serves 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine ingredients; beat with electric mixer 2 minutes.
Bake in 10-inch greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn bread muffins
directions: Mix together.
Pour in greased muffin pan.
Cook at 350° until golden brown.
Makes 18 to 20 large muffins.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix boiling water and flour.
Cook for 1 minute; add milk and egg yolks.
Cook until thick; add lemon juice and butter.
Cook a little longer.
Makes 1 pie.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on toast, bread, crackers or lettuce leaves.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Mix and heat for 1 hour.

title: creamed cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese and add other ingredients.
Form into a ball and roll in nuts.
Chill.

title: veal with creamy mustard sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 200 degrees.
On wax paper, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge veal in flour mixture, coating well on both sides.
In
9-inch skillet, heat oil over medium heat; add veal and cook 1-2 minutes each side, until brown.
Transfer veal to oven and keep warm.
In same skillet, heat margarine over high heat.
Saute mushroom and onion until lightly browned.
Reduce heat to low and add half and half, parsley, mustard and lemon juice, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and is thickened.
Pour over warm veal.

title: bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 2 loaves.

title: derek's south of the border casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; add green chiles and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add chili powder, salt and pepper.
Let simmer on low for 1/2 hour.
Stir in cream of mushroom soup.
In a separate casserole dish, layer the bottom with chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve with sour cream on top.

title: chocolate and cherry ring
directions: Mix oil, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in pie filling, chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a fluted tube pan.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool.
Sift powdered sugar on top.

title: london broil
directions: Combine all ingredients other than meat.
Let meat stand in marinade all day.
Sear meat in a frying pan on all sides.
Put in a hot oven (500°) and cook for 15 minutes.
The middle should be rare with the outside pieces more done.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil and cook 2 to 3 minutes or until sugars are dissolved.
Add vanilla and maple flavorings. Can be stored in cabinet or refrigerator.
Best when served warm.

title: boston bread
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins and let stand until cool. Cream sugar and butter together.
Add egg.
Sift together dry ingredietns and add to creamed mixture.
Add raisins, vanilla and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves or 4 cans (ungreased; use 1 pound coffee cans or vegetable cans).

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery in a small amount of water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Mix celery with chestnuts and soup.
Saute bread crumbs and almonds in margarine.
Place celery, chestnuts, and soup in a buttered casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You may add some of the bread crumbs and almonds into mix, but save some for topping.
Good with chicken or turkey.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Brown onion in oleo; add garlic salt.
Mix with rice and shrimp; add tomatoes and rest of seasonings.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: war cake
directions: Bring raisins, water, sugars, lard and cinnamon to a boil, turn heat down and boil for approximately 1 minute.
Turn off and cool completely.
Add baking soda, vanilla flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13 cake pan at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Stir together flour, brown sugar, nuts and melted butter. Spread 2/3 in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Reserve the rest for top.
Bake about 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Combine egg whites and sugar and whip to stiff peaks; add berries and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream; pour over crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Cover and freeze.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Pour buttermilk into well (hole) of flour in bowl (self-rising flour). Using spoon, gradually mix until good handling dough. Then pinch off and roll in both (cupped) hands. Place top side in pan to grease them all over. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: fried okra
directions: Mix okra and salt with enough corn meal to coat it.
Put in frying pan with hot oil.
Cook until brown or tender enough to eat.
Stir often.
Serve while hot.

title: hot peppers
directions: Put on rubber gloves; cut up peppers.
Add stuff and boil. Simmer 5 minutes.
After boil, seal in hot pint jars.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Heat drippings in saucepan.
Add other ingredients and simmer 2 or 3 minutes.
Add pork and simmer 5 to 10 minutes, longer if time permits.
Serve on buns or use as main dish.
The longer it simmers, the better it is.

title: london broil
directions: Combine all ingredients except steak and onions.
Place flank steak and onions in shallow glass dish.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Stir and quickly drop onto buttered cookie sheet.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternating with milk.
